ite web|url=http://iigea.com/amag/covid-19/ |title=COVID-19 Seguimiento \u2013 IIGEA |publisher=Iigea.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n</small>\n|}\n\n=== Cases per 100,000 inhabitants ===\n\n[[File:COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Mexico per 100,000 inhabitants.svg|thumb|right|251xpx| Map of the COVID-19 outbreak in Mexico per 100,000 inhabitants as of 2 April 2020.<br/>\n{{legend|#fee5d9|<0.1 per 100,000}}{{legend|#fcbba1|\u22650.1 per 100,000}}{{legend|#fc9272|\u22650.5 per 100,000}}{{legend|#fb6a4a|\u22651.0 per 100,000}}{{legend|#de2d26|\u22651.5 per 100,000}}{{legend|#a50f15|\u22652.0 per 100,000}}{{legend|#630606|\u22653.0 per 100,000}} {{legend|#450404|\u22655.0 per 100,000}} {{legend|#310303|\u22657.0 per 100,000}}]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"display: inline-table; font-size:90%; text-align:right;\"\n|+ <big> As of April 3</big>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"  style=\"text-align:left; width:140px;\"|State\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Cases\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" | Population{{efn|In 2015.}}\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" | Cases per 100,000 inhabitants{{efn|Calculated by dividing the number of cases by the total population of the state and multiplying the result by 100,000.}}\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:18px;\" scope=\"row\" | 1688\n! style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:18px;\" scope=\"row\" | 119,530,753\n! style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:18px;\" scope=\"row\" | 1.4\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Mexico City}}\n||384||8,918,653||4.3\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Quintana Roo}}\n||65||1,501,562||4.3\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Aguascalientes}}\n||48||1,312,544||3.7\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Tabasco}}\n||73||2,395,272||3.0\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Baja California Sur}}\n||21||712,029||2.9\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Yucat\u00e1n}}\n||58||2,097,175||2.8\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Coahuila}}\n||70||2,954,915||2.4\n|-\n