span=\"6\"| '''Source:''' \n<small>Secretariat of Health (2020).<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/><br>\nGeological and Atmospheric Research Institute <ref name=\"iigea1\"/><br>National Institute of Statistics and Geography <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cuentame.inegi.org.mx/poblacion/habitantes.aspx?tema=P |title=N\u00famero de habitantes. Cu\u00e9ntame de M\u00e9xico |publisher=Cuentame.inegi.org.mx |date=2005-04-02 |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Curve of infection ===\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=600\n|height=400\n|colors=#FF4343\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|yAxisTitle=No. of cases\n|legend=Legend\n<!-- PLease clipboard copy the \"}x=...\" and \"y1=...\" lines from the log plot of total cases when you update these charts -->\n\n<!-- Search string CASES_X -->\n|x= Feb 28, Feb 29, Mar 1, Mar 6, Mar 7, Mar 11, Mar 12, Mar 13, Mar 14, Mar 15, Mar 16, Mar 17, Mar 18, Mar 19, Mar 20, Mar 21, Mar 22, Mar 23, Mar 24, Mar 25, Mar 26, Mar 27, Mar 28, Mar 29, Mar 30, Mar 32, Apr 1, Apr 2, Apr 3, Apr 4\n\n<!-- Search string CASES_Y -->\n|y1= 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 11, 15, 26, 41, 53, 82, 93, 118, 164, 203, 251, 316, 367, 405, 475, 585, 717, 848, 993, 1094, 1215, 1378, 1510, 1688, 1890\n\n|yScaleType=<!--log This is the line that makes this plot have a log axis, so leave it blank here!-->\n|y1Title=Total confirmed cases\n|yGrid= |xGrid=\n}}\n\n== Phases ==\nAccording to the Secretariat of Health, there are three phases before the disease (COVID-19) can be considered as an epidemic in the country:<ref name=\"phases\">{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexicos-covid-19-contingency-plan-three-key-phases-fight-coronavirus-outbreak|title= Mexico's covid-19 contingency plan: three key phases to fight the coronavirus outbreak|author=Teresa Moreno|date=March 14, 2020|website=El Universal}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"display: inline-table; font-size:90%; text-align:right;\"\n|-\n! colspan =\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | Phase\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | Time period\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | Description \n! rowspan=\"2\" | Ref\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | Start \n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | End\n|-\n! 1\u00b0\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | Viral Import\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | February 28, 2020\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | March 23, 2020<ref name=\"phase2\">{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/covid-19-mexico-has-entered-second-phase-its-contingency-plan |title= Covid-19: mexico has entered the second phase of its contingency plan |author=Newsroom & Agencies|date=March 24, 2020|website=El Universal}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | \n*People with the virus caught the disease outside Mexico and there are no cases of local transmission.\n*There is a limited number of people infected with the virus.\n*There are no strict restrictions for greeting people. \n*Public events in closed or open spaces are still allowed.\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:left\" | <ref name=\"phases\" />\n|-\n! 2\u00b0\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | Community Transmission\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | March 24, 2020<ref name=\"phase2\" />\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | [[TBA]]\n| style=\"text-align:left\" |\n* Community transmission cases are reported between people who have not had contact with foreigners.\n*The number of confirmed cases increases rapidly.\n*Massive public events are canceled both in open and closed spaces.\n*School classes are suspended and people are encouraged to work from home. \n|-\n! 3\u00b0\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | Epidemic\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | [[TBA]]\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | [[TBA]]\n| style=\"text-align:left\" |\n* Thousands of cases are reported in multiple locations across the country.\n*Schools and workplaces with active outbreaks would have no activities.\n* It requires the implementation of stricter health protocols.\n* In the worst case scenario it would be required a general quarantine of the population.\n|}\n\n==Economic effects==\n{{See also|Socio-economic impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|Financial impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\nThe [[National Institute of Statistics and Geography (Mexico)|INEGI]] says the unemployment rate increased from 3.6% in January 2020 to 3.7% in February 2020. The informal sector increased to 56.3% in February compared to 56.0% in February 2019.<ref>[https://www.tvazteca.com/aztecanoticias/finanzas/notas/aumenta-el-desempleo-en-mexico?fbclid=IwAR2eO0b2MXeWkJ0JegBEJNrXILvvAH1frrw1IFAF47gKBLfQoAVBA5LaJas Unemployment increases in Mexico] {{in lang|es}} Azteca Noticias, 26 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nThe [[Mexican Stock Exchange]] fell to a record low on 10 March due to fears of the coronavirus and because of [[2020 Russia\u2013Saudi Arabia oil price war|falling oil prices]]. The [[Bank of Mexico|Bank of Mexico (Banxico)]] stepped in to prop up the value of the peso, which fell 14% to 22.929 per US dollar.<ref name=\"banixco\"/> World markets are seeing falls similar to those of 1987.<ref>[https://www.dineroenimagen.com/blogs/colegio-de-contadores-publicos-de-mexico-ac/historico-el-covid-19-provoca-la-mayor-crisis-en Historical! COVID-19 causes the biggest crisis in global financial markets] {{in lang|es}} by COLEGIO DE CONTADORES P\u00daBLICOS DE M\u00c9XICO, A.C., Dinero en Imagen, 18 Mar 2020</ref> [[Moody's Investors Service]] predicted that the economy will contract 5.2% during the first trimester of the year and 3.7% by the end of the year.<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/25/economia-de-mexico-caera-37-por-coronavirus-moodys/ Mexico's economy will drop 3.7% due to coronavirus: Moody\u2019s] {{in lang|es}} Infobae, 25 Mar 2020</ref> Banxico announced on 1 April that foreign investors have withdrawn MXN $150 billion (US $,6.3 billion) from Mexico, mostly in ''Certificados de la Tesorer\u00eda'' ((Treasury Certificates, Cetes) since February 27 when the first COVID-19 case in Mexico was diagnosed. The problem is compounded by the low oil price, only US $10.37 per barrel, a 20.29% drop since the beginning of the [[2020 Russia\u2013Saudi Arabia oil price war]].<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/04/01/coronavirus-en-mexico-extranjeros-retiran-150-mmdp-del-pais-por-covid-19/ Coronavirus in Mexico: foreigners withdraw 150 mmdp from the country for COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} Infoabe Mexico, 1 April 2020</ref> \n\nOn 24 March, [[Grupo Modelo]], makers of [[Corona (beer)|Corona beer]], promised to donate 300,000 bottles of antibacterial gel to the [[Mexican Social Security Institute|Mexican Social Security Institute (IMSS)]].<ref>[https://www.sinembargo.mx/24-03-2020/3754411?fbclid=IwAR2qx4vzr-sOgF5mF2IjD2EFAz5_Tq-OZAFpF6irpufZBsavsysjswaMYLk Grupo Modelo donar\u00e1 300 mil botellas de gel antibacterial al IMSS para combatir al COVID-19]{{in lang|es}} Sin Embargo, 24 Mar 2020</ref> The ''Conacintra'' (National Chamber of the Processing Industry) announced on 2 April they were suspending all beer production in the country, as breweries are not an essential industry and there was sufficient supply in the country for a month.<ref>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/cartera/coronavirus-no-se-producira-cerveza-durante-un-mes-informa-canacintra Beer will not be produced for a month; Not an essential activity: Canacintra] {{in lang|es}} El Universal, 2 Apr 2020</ref> Tequila producers plan to stay open.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-mexico-tequila/mexican-tequila-makers-unlike-brewers-plan-to-keep-up-production-exports-idUSKBN21M0SU Mexican tequila makers, unlike brewers, plan to keep up production, exports] Reuters, 4 Apr 2020</ref>\n\nThe ''Consejo Nacional Empresarial Tur\u00edstico'' (National Tourism Business Council, CNET) sent two letters in March to [[Alfonso Romo]], Chief of Staff to the President, outlining the importance of tourism to the economy and asking for government support for the sector. Tourism provides 4 million jobs in Mexico, and 93% of the companies have ten or fewer employees. COVID-19 has forced the closure of 4,000 hotels (52,400 rooms) and 2,000 restaurants, while the airline industry has lost MXN $30 billion (US $1.3 billion).<ref>[https://www.dineroenimagen.com/carlos-velazquez/el-cnet-pide-apoyo-mientras-sus-empresas-salvan-empleos/120918 The CNET asks for support while their companies save jobs] {{in lang|en}} by Carlos Velazquez, Dinero en Imagen, 26 Mar 2020</ref> Tourism accounts for 10% of [[Gross domestic product|Gross domestic product (GDP)]] in the world.<ref>[https://www.dineroenimagen.com/maricarmen-cortes/turismo-en-riesgo-el-10-del-pib-mundial/120916 Tourism: 10% of world GDP at risk] {{in lang|en}} by Maricarmen Cortes, Dinero en Imagen, 26 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nThe association of car dealers, ADMA, predicts a decrease in sales in Mexico between 16% and 25% this year.<ref>[https://www.dineroenimagen.com/jose-yuste/desesperacion-de-industrias/120857?utm_source=dineroenimagen_desktop&utm_campaign=relacionados&utm_medium=article Despair of industries] {{in lang|en}} by Jos\u00e9 Yuste, Dinero en Imagen, 25 Mar 2020</ref> [[J.D. Power]] estimated a 20% decrease, 264,000 vehicles, in Mexico and a 15% drop across the world.<ref>[https://www.forbes.com.mx/economia-caida-venta-autos-mexico-20-coronavirus/ Car sales in Mexico will fall 20% due to coronavirus: JD Power] {{in lang|es}} Forbes Mexico, 1 April 2020</ref> The [[Coparmex|Employers Confederation of the Mexican Republic (COPARMEX)]] criticized the government on 29 March for not suspending the payment of taxes, saying the government does not care about unemployment. Fernando Trevi\u00f1o N\u00fa\u00f1ez, president of the organization, explained that businesses cannot afford to pay salaries for more than three months without receiving income.<ref>[https://www.milenio.com/negocios/sin-rumbo-el-gobierno-federal-ante-la-pandemia-coparmex Sin rumbo, el gobierno federal ante la pandemia: Coparmex] {{in lang|es}} by  Ang\u00e9lica Tenahua, Milenio, 29 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nPanic buying in mid-March is causing shortages in Mexico of [[Hydroxychloroquine]] and [[azithromycin]], which U.S. President Donald Trump, with no backing from the scientific or medical communities, says is helpful in preventing COVID-19. The ''Comisi\u00f3n Federal para la Protecci\u00f3n de Riesgos Sanitarios'' (Federal Commission for the Protection of Health Risks, Cofepris) has put controls on the sale of both products. Hidroxicloroquina is used in the treatment of [[malaria]], [[lupus]] and [[rheumatoid arthritis]]. Plaquenil tablets are produced in Mexico by the French company [[Sanofi]]; the raw material comes from [[Hungary]]. Shortages of medicine for these diseases can be expected soon.<ref name=panic>[https://www.dineroenimagen.com/jose-yuste/compras-de-panico-escasean-la-hidroxicloroquina/120913 Compras de p\u00e1nico escasean la hidroxicloroquina] {{in lang|en}} by Jos\u00e9 Yuste, Dinero en Imagen, 26 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nGasoline and diesel fuel importers have not noted a decrease in demand since the onset of the COVID-19 pandemic, and they fear that health precautions could cause fuel delays at ports of entry. [[Watco Companies]] said that cargo on the [[Houston Ship Channel]] for delivery to San Luis Potos\u00ed increased 25% in March compared to January. Mexico imports 65% of its gasoline.<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/26/crecen-temores-entre-importadores-de-gasolina-por-caida-en-la-demanda/ Fears Grow Among Gasoline Importers Due to Demand Drop] {{in lang|en}} By Amy Stillman & Jeffrey Bair, Bloomberg/Inforbae, 26 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nSome financial analysts say there has been too little, too late. Carlos Serrano of [[BBVA M\u00e9xico]] predicts a 4.5% economic contraction in 2020, while analysts at [[Capital Economics]] in London argue that the government has to do more to support the economy. They forecast a 6% contraction this year. HR Ratings, Latin America\u2019s first credit rating agency, said that the performance of the economy this year will depend on the government\u2019s response to the COVID-19 crisis.<ref>{{cite web |website=Mexico News Daily|title=While WHO praises virus response, financial analysts say it's too slow|date=March 26, 2020|language=en |url=https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/coronavirus/who-praises-virus-response/}}</ref>\n\t\nAuthorities are concerned about supermarket robberies. A gang of 70 people robbed a grocery store in [[Tec\u00e1mac]], State of Mexico, on March 23, and a gang of 30 looted a supermarket in [[Oaxaca City]] on March 24. Calls for supermarket looting, warning of food shortages, are making the rounds of social media.<ref>[https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/30-break-into-and-loot-oaxaca-supermarket-2/ 30 people break into and loot Oaxaca supermarket] Mexico News Daily, 25 Mar 2020  [https://apnews.com/5625bb27578887acbb834bd99bfccaaa Mexico police investigate store robberies as virus spreads] AP, 25 March 2020</ref> Four such social media groups in Tijuana were broken up in Baja California on 29 March.<ref>[https://www.msn.com/es-mx/noticias/mexico/frustran-saqueos-a-tiendas-en-tijuana/ar-BB11SNZj Frustran saqueos a tiendas en Tijuana] {{in lang|es}} Excelsior, 29 Mar 2020</ref>\n\n==Government response==\n*9 January, 2020 \u2013 A travel advisory for people traveling to or from China was issued.<ref name=indigo />\n*22 January \u2013 The [[Secretariat of Health (Mexico)|Secretariat of Health]] issued a statement saying that the novel coronavirus COVID-19 did not present a danger to Mexico.<ref name=indigo>{{cite web |url=https://www.reporteindigo.com/piensa/el-nuevo-virus-coronavirus-no-representa-un-peligro-para-mexico/ |title=El Nuevo Virus Coronavirus No Representa Un Peligro Para M\u00e9xico |trans-title=The New Coronavirus Does Not Represent a Danger for Mexico |language=Spanish |work=Reporte de Indigo |date=22 January 2020 |access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n*30 January \u2013 The Government of Mexico designed a ''Preparation and Response Plan'' that was made by the National Committee for Health Safety, a working group led by Secretariat of Health composed by different health entities aiming to act upon the imminent arrival of the pandemic. This group carried out a series of alert measures, rehabilitation and updating of epidemiological regulations based on the International Health Regulations.<ref name=salud>{{cite web|url=http://www.gob.mx/salud/prensa/033-mexico-esta-preparado-para-enfrentar-coronavirus-2019-ncov|title=M\u00e9xico est\u00e1 preparado para enfrentar coronavirus (2019-nCoV) (Mexico is prepared to face coronavirus)|publisher=Secretariat of Health|date=|website=gob.mx|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n*5 March \u2013 The National Governors' Conference (Conago) met to discuss the coronavirus outbreak. The directors of INSABI, IMSS and ISSSTE also participated.<ref name=conago/>\n*6 March \u2013 [[Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell Ram\u00edrez]] led the first daily press conference on COVID-19.<ref name=nat_coun_health />\n*10 March \u2013 As the stock market and the price of oil fell, \u2018\u2018Banxico\u2019\u2019 stepped in to prop up the value of the peso, which had fallen 14%.<ref name=banixco />\n*13 March \u2013 The National Autonomous University of Mexico suspended in-person classes. Authorities canceled or postponed major tourist events in Guadalajara and Merida.<ref name=cancelations />\n*14 March\n**The SEP announced that all sporting and civic events in schools would be canceled<ref name=sep /> and that Easter break, originally planned from 6 to 17 April, would be extended from 20 March to 20 April.<ref name=\"Prevention Easter break in schools\" /> On 31 March the school closings were extended through 30 April.<ref>[https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Casos-positivos-de-COVID-19-en-Mexico-ascienden-a-mil-215-20200331-0171.html Positive cases of COVID-19 in Mexico amount to 1,215] {{in lang|es}} Informador, 31 Mar 2020</ref>\n**The SCHP announced it was taking measures to prevent a 0.5% fall in GDP.<ref name=schp /> \n**The \u2018\u2018Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de Nuevo Le\u00f3n\u2019\u2019 (UANL) suspended classes for its more than 206,000 students starting on March 17.<ref name=uanl />\n*15 March \u2013 [[List of heads of government of Mexico City|Mexico City mayor]] Claudia Sheinbaum declared that Mexico City expected to spend an extra MXN $100 million to prevent the spread of COVID-19.<ref name=sheinbaum />\n*18 March \u2013 Authorities announced that they were looking for hundreds of citizens who might be carriers of the coronavirus, especially in the states of Puebla, Jalisco, Aguascalientes and Guerrero. The Autonomous University of Guerrero (UAGRO) in Chilpancingo closed after a female student tested positive for the virus.<ref name=look />\n*22 March\n**Bars, nightclubs, movie theaters and museums were closed in Mexico City.<ref name=bars /> \n**Governor Alfaro Ram\u00edrez announces that [[Jalisco]] and seven other states would block flights from areas such as that had a high rate of coronavirus. He also said that they would purchase 25,000 testing kits.<ref name=planes />\n**Governor [[Jaime Rodr\u00edguez Calder\u00f3n]] of Nuevo Le\u00f3n said he will not rule out the use of force to get people to stay at home.<ref>[https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/el-bronco-no-descarta-usar-fuerza-publica-para-que-se-cumpla-aislamiento/1371423 \u2018El Bronco\u2019 no descarta usar fuerza p\u00fablica para que se cumpla aislamiento] {{in lang|es}} by ARACELY GARZA, Reuters/Excelsior, 22 Mar 2020, retrieved 28 Mar 2020</ref>\n*23 March\n**The WHO announced that Mexico had entered into the community contact phase of infection.<ref name=who />\n**The National Campaign of Healthy Distancing, a national program of non-pharmaceutical measures based on [[social distancing]], began.<ref name=social/> A media campaign led by \"Susana Distancia\", who is a fictional female superhero aiming to promote social distancing, was launched.<ref name=susana /> \"Susana Distancia\" is in fact a [[Word play|wordplay]] roughly meaning \"(maintaining) a healthy distance\".\n**Access to supermarkets, drugstores and convenience stores in Coahuila was limited to one person per family, and the temperature of that person was taken before entering.<ref name=supermarket />\n*24 March \u2013 President [[Andr\u00e9s Manuel L\u00f3pez Obrador|L\u00f3pez Obrador]] announced that Mexico had entered Phase 2 of the coronavirus pandemic, in effect until April 30. Gatherings of more than 100 people were prohibited, and both the [[Mexican Army]] and the [[Mexican Navy]] would participate.<ref name=amlo_phase2 />\n*25 March\n**President L\u00f3pez Obrador ordered the Mexican Air Force to rescue Mexicans trapped in Argentina.<ref name=airforce /> \n**[[PROFECO|Office of the Federal Prosecutor for the Consumer (Profeco)]] closed two businesses in [[Tijuana]], Baja California, for price-gouging.<ref name=profecobc /> \n**In Mexico City, Claudia Sheinbaum announced financial support for families and micro industries affected by the pandemic, and she suspended automobile smog checks through April 19. She closed movie theaters, bars, nightclubs, gyms and other entertainment centers.<ref name=finsupport />\n**The government announced that it would continue receiving [[2020 coronavirus pandemic on cruise ships|cruise ships]] \u201cfor humanitarian reasons,\u201d but that passengers would be individually \"fumigated\" before being taken directly to airports to be returned to their home countries. The protocol will apply to the {{ship|MS|Europa}}, currently docked in Puerta Vallarta.<ref name=sea>[https://apnews.com/01aea6b6217f0464be47180c27af389f Mexico will receive cruise ships, but fumigate passengers] AP, 25 Mar 2020</ref>\n*26 March\n**President L\u00f3pez Obrador addressed the [[G20|Group of Twenty]] regarding medical supplies and trade and tariffs.<ref name=g20 /> The federal government announced it would suspend most sectors' activities from 26 March to 19 April.<ref name=suspend_govt /> \n**The Secretary of Health estimated that Phase 3 of the pandemic, when the number of cases reaches its peak, will be about 19 April.<ref name=peak /> \n**Authorities in Chihuahua announced that it would start to quarantine migrants who were returned to the Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez border crossing.<ref name=chi />\n**The ''Comisi\u00f3n Federal para la Protecci\u00f3n de Riesgos Sanitarios'' (Federal Commission for the Protection of Health Risks, Cofepris) put controls on the sale of hidroxicloroquina and azithromycin, used in the treatment of malaria, lupus]] and rheumatoid arthritis, but not shown to be effective against [[COVID-19]]. Nonetheless, panic buying of these medicines is likely to soon lead to a shortage.<ref name=panic />\n*27 March\n** President L\u00f3pez Obrador practiced social distancing during his tour in [[Nayarit]]. The president had been widely criticized for shaking hands, kissing and hugging as he met with people.<ref name=distance>[https://politica.expansion.mx/presidencia/2020/03/27/en-gira-por-nayarit-amlo-aplica-sana-distancia-recomendada-por-coronavirus En gira por Nayarit, AMLO aplica \"sana distancia\" recomendada por coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} Expansi\u00f3n Politica, 27 Mar 2020</ref>\n**The federal government bought 5,000 [[ventilator]]s from China.<ref name=ventilator>[https://politica.expansion.mx/presidencia/2020/03/27/gobierno-compra-5-000-ventiladores-a-china-para-enfrentar-coronavirus Gobierno compra 5,000 ventiladores a China para enfrentar coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} Expansi\u00f3n Politica, 27 Mar 2020</ref>\n**Profeco (Office of the Federal Prosecutor for the Consumer) announced it would fine merchants who unfairly raised the prices on household goods.<ref name=fine />\n**[[V\u00edctor Villalobos Ar\u00e1mbula]], [[Secretariat of Agriculture and Rural Development (Mexico)|Secretary of Agriculture and Rural Development (SADER)]] met with food producers to discuss guaranteeing the food supply in spite of the pandemic.<ref>[https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/economia/2020/03/27/sader-delimita-acciones-para-garantizar-abasto-de-alimentos-6457.html Sader delimita acciones para garantizar abasto de alimentos] {{in lang|es}} by  Carolina G\u00f3mez Mena, La Jornada, 27 Mar 2020</ref>\n*March 28\n**[[Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell Ram\u00edrez]], Deputy Secretary of Health, said that with 16 deaths and 848 cases of infection, this is the last opportunity to prevent accelerated growth of COVID-19. He called on the population to act responsibly to prevent its spread.<ref>[https://aristeguinoticias.com/2803/mexico/ultima-oportunidad-de-evitar-crecimiento-acelerado-de-covid-19-lopez-gatell-van-16-muertes-y-848-contagiados/ \u00daltima oportunidad de evitar crecimiento acelerado de COVID-19: L\u00f3pez-Gatell; van 16 muertes y 848 contagiados] {{in lang|es}} Arestegui Noticias, 28 Mar 2020</ref> ''[[Milenio]]'' reported that L\u00f3pez-Gatell said there is a legal basis for the use of force to enforce stay-at-home orders during the COVID-19 pandemic.<ref>[https://www.milenio.com/politica/covid-19-fuerza-publica-mantener-gente-casa?fbclid=IwAR04pAvd6BR_KgpwKq1ENodfpqbP7D_-isW2C01gBO09mXE9641H_gc1Pig \u00daltima oportunidad para permanecer en casa: L\u00f3pez Gatell] {{in lang|es}} by Fanny Miranda, Milenio, 28 Mar 2020</ref>\n**Health officials, accompanied by a representative of the military and Foreign Secretary [[Marcelo Ebrard]] made a video urging the populace to stay home. AMLO did not appear in that video, but he made a separate one with the same message.<ref>[https://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/news/border-baja-california/story/2020-03-28/in-tijuana-video-address-mexicos-president-toughens-coronavirus-stance In Tijuana video address, Mexico\u2019s president toughens coronavirus stance] {{in lang|en}} By WENDY FRY, The San Diego Union-Tribune, 28 Mar 2020</ref>\n*30 March \u2013 A national health emergency was declared in Mexico and stricter measures aimed at containing the spread of the virus were introduced.<ref name=\"30march\" />\n*1 April\n**Beaches throughout the country are closed.<ref>[https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Anuncia-Salud-cierre-de-playas-ante-emergencia-por-COVID-19-20200401-0016.html Anuncia Salud cierre de playas ante emergencia por COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} Notimex/Informador, 1 April 2020</ref>\n**INEGI asked everyone who has not taken part of the 2020 census to contact them via their webpage or by calling them before 15 April.<ref>[https://www.milenio.com/politica/comunidad/coronavirus-inegi-pide-entregar-informacion-internet Inegi pide a ciudadanos censarse por internet antes del 15 de abril] {{in lang|es}} Milenio, 1 April 2020</ref>\n**The [[Governor of Nuevo Le\u00f3n]] ordered a halt to production and distribution of beer in the state, beginning April 3.<ref>[https://www.forbes.com.mx/economia-gobierno-nuevo-leon-anuncia-paro-produccion-distribucion-cerveza-pais/?fbclid=IwAR2zgxuKOiLAUhzQ44bbhpf-I1_S461Doh-QPdobMaMDLvm8ZclmNr9egvU NL government anticipates high production and distribution of alcoholic beverages throughout the country] {{in lang|es}} Forbes Mexico, 1 April 2020</ref>\n*3 April \u2013 AMLO issues a decree to abolish 100 public trusts related to science and culture; the [[Secretariat of Finance and Public Credit|Fianance Ministry (SHCP) will receive the money directly.<ref>[https://www.la-prensa.com.mx/mexico/politica/amlo-emite-decreto-para-extincion-de-fideicomisos-publicos-5053897.html AMLO issues decree for the extinction of public trusts] {{in lang|es}} by Carlos Lara, El Sol de M\u00e9xico, 3 Apr 2020</ref> The move is expected to MXN save $250 billion (US $10 billion) which can be spent to strengthen the economy, pay for social programs and pay off the debt.<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/finanzas/con-extincion-de-fideicomisos-se-ahorraran-250-mil-mdp-amlo-5054241.html With extinction of trusts 250 thousand mp will be saved: AMLO] {{in lang|es}} by Sarahi Uribe, El Sol de M\u00e9xico, 3 Apr 2020</ref>\n*Claudia Sheinbaum promised to donate two months of her salary (a total of MXN $156,728) to the struggle against COVID-19 and invited other officials to do so also.<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/sheinbaum-donara-dos-meses-de-su-salario-para-enfrentar-covid-19-5058851.html Sheinbaum donar\u00e1 dos meses de su salario para enfrentar Covid-19] {{in lang|es}} by Israel Zamarr\u00f3n, El Sol de M\u00e9xico, 4 Apr 2020</ref>\n\n==Cancellations, suspensions, and closings==\n{{Main|List of events affected by the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{See also|Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education|Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports|Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema}}\n\n;Archaeological sites\nTeotihuac\u00e1n, Xochicalco, El Tepozteco closed 21\u201322 March. Chich\u00e9n Itz\u00e1 closed indefinitely starting 21 March.<ref name=inah />\n;Educational institutions\n:'''Basic education'''The SEP announced on 14 March that all sporting and civic events in schools would be cancelled<ref name=sep /> and that Easter break would be from 20 March to 20 April.<ref name=\"Prevention Easter break in schools\" /> \n:'''Higher education''': The [[National Autonomous University of Mexico|UNAM]] and [[Monterrey Institute of Technology and Higher Education|Tec de Monterrey]], switched to virtual classes on 13 March.<ref name=cancelations /> Autonomous University of the State of Morelos, (UAEM) suspended classes on 16 March.<ref name=uaem /> Autonomous University of Nuevo Leon, (UANL) suspended classes from 17 March to 20 April.<ref name=uanl /> Autonomous University of Guerrero (UAGRO) and Technical Institute of Guerrero ([[Chilpancingo]]) closed 18 March.<ref name=look />\n;Entertainment\n[[Grupo CIE|OCESA]] cancelled all its events until April 19.<ref name=ocesa>{{cite web|website=El Universal|language=es|trans-title=Ocesa suspends all its events until April 19 due to the coronavirus|title=Ocesa suspende todos sus eventos hasta el 19 de abril por el coronavirus |date=March 16, 2020|accessdate=March 29, 2020|url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/espectaculos/musica/ocesa-suspende-sus-eventos-hasta-el-19-de-abril-por-el-coronavirus}}</ref>\n:'''Fairs''': Authorities announced on 14 March they were considering the cancellation of the ''Festival Internacional de Cine de Guadalajara''. In M\u00e9rida, the ''Tianguis Tur\u00edstico'' was postponed to September.<ref name=cancelations /> \n:'''Musical''': ''[[Chicago (musical)|Chicago]]'' suspended until 17 April<ref name=ocesa />\n:'''Concerts''': [[The Magic Numbers]], [[Los Tigres del Norte]], Red Orange County {{sic}}, [[Mercury Rev]], Mar\u00eda Le\u00f3n, [[Sasha Sloan]]<ref name=ocesa /> and [[Ricky Martin]]<ref>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/espectaculos/musica/coronavirus-ricky-martin-cancela-conciertos-en-mexico Ricky Martin cancels all his concerts in Mexico due to coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} El Universal, 13 Mar 2020</ref>\n:'''Conference''': [[Michelle Obama]]<ref name=ocesa />\n:'''Other''': Bars, nightclubs, movie theaters, and museums were closed in Mexico City on 22 March.<ref name=bars />\n;Government\nPresident L\u00f3pez Obrador suspended non-essential activities from 26 March to 19 April. The health and energy sectors, the oil industry, and public services such as water supply, waste management and public safety continued to function.<ref name=suspend_govt />\n;Industry\nFord Motor Company, Honda and Audi closed their manufacturing plants in Mexico on 18 March.<ref name=ford /> Hundreds of hotel employees in [[Canc\u00fan]] were fired.<ref name=cancun /> Alsea ([[Starbucks]], VIPS, [[Domino's Pizza]], [[Burger King]], Italianni's, [[Chili's]], [[California Pizza Kitchen]], [[P. F. Chang's China Bistro]] and [[The Cheesecake Factory]]) offered its employees unpaid leave.<ref name=alsea /> PROFECO closed two businesses in Tijuana Baja California, for price-gouging on 25 March.<ref name=profecobc /> [[Cin\u00e9polis]] announced that they will temporaily close all of their theaters starting March 25.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cin\u00e9polis regresar\u00e1 el dinero de boletos programados |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/espectaculos/cine/cinepolis-regresara-el-dinero-de-boletos-programados|website=El Universal|date=March 24, 2020|access-date=March 25, 2020|language=es}}</ref>\n;Ports of entry\n:'''Air''': Governor Alfaro Ram\u00edrez of Jalisco announced that beginning Thursday, 26 March, eight states in the [[Baj\u00edo]] and western Mexico woud block flights from areas that had a high rate of coronavirus. The restrictions would apply at the [[Miguel Hidalgo y Costilla Guadalajara International Airport]] and the [[Licenciado Gustavo D\u00edaz Ordaz International Airport]] in Puerto Vallarta.<ref name=planes />\n:'''Land''': The [[United States Department of State]] announced on 20 March there would be restrictions on travel across the Mexico\u2013United States border. The restrictions would not apply to cargo.<ref name=pompeo /> On 26 March, protesters in Sonora insisted that the government limit [[Mexico\u2013United States border|border crossings]] with the United States.<ref name=border /> Chihuahua (state) announced that it would start to quarantine migrants who are returned to the Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez border crossing.<ref name=chi /> Citizens of Nogales, Sonora, blocked border crossing from Nogales, Arizona, in order to prevent the entrance of individuals with the virus infection and to prevent shortages of food, bottled water, toilet paper and cleaning supplies in local stores.<ref name=nogales />\n:'''Sea''': The government announced on 25 March it would continue receiving cruise ships but that passengers would be individually \"fumigated\" before being taken directly to airports to be returned to their home countries.<ref name=sea />\n;Sports\n[[Jalisco Open]] (tennis tournament) and [[CONCACAF Champions League]] (soccer) cancelled 13 March<ref name=cancelations />\n;Religious events\nOn 17 March, [[Passion Play of Iztapalapa]] in Mexico City moved to an undisclosed location indoors and televised on April 10<ref>{{cite web|website=[[La Jornada]]|title=Suspenden Viacrucis de Iztapalapa; actos a puerta cerrada y v\u00eda tv |language=es|trans-title=Way of the Cross of Iztapalapa suspended; acts behind closed doors and via tv|date=March 17, 2020|accessdate=March 29, 2020 |url=https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/capital/2020/03/17/cancelan-viacrucis-de-iztapalapa-5742.html}}</ref>\n\nSan Luis Potosi suspended wakes and funerals on March 29.<ref name=funeral />\n;Curfew established\nMayor Juanita Romero ([[National Action Party (Mexico)|PAN]]) of Nacozari de Garc\u00eda, Sonora, declared a curfew in effect until 20 April.<ref name=curfew />\n\n== Notable Mexicans with COVID-19 ==\n{{Div col}}\n*Alejandra Ag\u00fcayo, newscaster ([[FOROtv]])<ref name=famous>[https://www.infobae.com/america/entretenimiento/2020/03/27/famosos-mexicanos-con-coronavirus-y-como-enfrentan-su-aislamiento/ Famous Mexicans with coronaviruses and how they face their isolation] {{in lang|es}} Infobae, 27 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Jorge Alcib\u00edades Garcia, [[Chamber of Deputies (Mexico)|federal deputy]]<ref name=mil />\n*[[Esteban Arce]], newscaster (''Expreso de la ma\u00f1ana'')<ref name=famous />\n*Mariana Arceo, Mexican [[Pentathlon|pentathelete]] ([[Mexico at the 2020 Summer Olympics|2020 Olympic Team]])<ref name=mil>[https://www.milenio.com/espectaculos/coronavirus-politicos-famosos-y-deportistas-que-han-dado-positivo Athletes, politicians and celebrities who have tested positive for coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} Milenio, 26 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Juan Domingo Beckmann, businessperson ([[Jose Cuervo]] tequila)<ref name=placido />\n*[[Patricio Borghetti]], television presenter (''Venga la Alegr\u00eda''; TV Azteca)<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/america/entretenimiento/2020/03/26/nada-que-un-taco-no-solucione-otro-dia-en-la-cuarentena-por-coronavirus-de-odalys-ramirez-y-patricio-borghetti/ \"Nothing that a taco does not solve\": another day in the quarantine for coronavirus of Odalys Ram\u00edrez and Patricio Borghetti] {{in lang|es}} Infobae, 26 Mar 2020</ref>\n*[[Placido Domingo]], 79, Spanish tenor who lives in Mexico<ref name=placido>[https://www.lavanguardia.com/musica/20200328/48130404682/placido-domingo-coronavirus.html Pl\u00e1cido Domingo, admitted to Acapulco for complications associated with Covid-19] {{in lang|es}} La Vanguardia, 28 Mar 2020</ref>\n*[[Francisco Dom\u00ednguez Servi\u00e9n]], [[Governor of Quer\u00e9taro]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.radioformula.com.mx/noticias/20200330/francisco-dominguez-servien-coronavirus-covid-19-gobernador-queretaro-mexico/|date=30 March 2020|title=Gobernador de Quer\u00e9taro da positivo en coronavirus|agency=radioformula|author=Itzel Garc\u00eda}} {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n*[[Omar Fayad]], [[List of Governors of Hidalgo|Governor of Hidalgo]]<ref>[https://politica.expansion.mx/estados/2020/03/28/el-gobernador-de-hidalgo-omar-fayad-esta-enfermo-de-coronavirus-amlo-mananera-covid-19 The Governor of Hidalgo, Omar Fayad, is sick with coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} Expansi\u00f3n Politica, 28 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Horacio Franco, flautist and director (''Capella Varroca M\u00e9xico'')<ref name=famous />\n*Mar\u00eda Fritz Sierra, General Secretary of the government of [[Yucatan]]<ref>https://www.milenio.com/politica/coronavirus-mexico-31-marzo-casos-noticias-hora-vivo Secretary General of the Yucatan government tests positive for COVID-19] Milenio, 31 Mar 2020</ref>{{better source|date=April 2020}}\n*[[Danna Garc\u00eda]], Colombian actress who resides in Mexico (''El Se\u00f1or de los Cielos'')<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/america/entretenimiento/2020/03/16/danna-garcia-dio-positivo-a-coronavirus-se-mantiene-en-aislamiento-pero-optimista/ Danna Garc\u00eda tested positive for coronavirus: remains in isolation, but optimistic] {{in lang|es}} Infobae, 16 Mar 2020, retrieved 29 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Mar\u00eda Libier Gonz\u00e1lez Anaya, federal deputy<ref name=dep />\n*[[Jolette (singer)|Jolette]], singer, television presenter, and reality star (''[[La Academia]]'' 2005)<ref name=razon>[https://www.razon.com.mx/entretenimiento/ellos-son-los-famosos-en-mexico-que-se-han-infectado-de-covid-19/ These are the famous Mexicans who have been infected with COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} La Raz\u00f3n, 27 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Jos\u00e9 Kuri Harfush, businessperson ([[Inbursa]])<ref name=univision />\n*Hilde Lara, singer with Yndio<ref name=famous /> \n*[[Ad\u00e1n Augusto L\u00f3pez Hern\u00e1ndez]], [[Governor of Tabasco]]<ref name=loppez_hernandez />\n*Alberto Marrero, businessperson (CEO [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]])<ref name=mil />\n*Audomaro P\u00e9rez, 72, bass player ([[Yndio]])<ref name=famous />\n*Mar\u00eda de Jes\u00fas Rosete S\u00e1nchez, federal deputy<ref name=dep>[https://www.msn.com/es-mx/noticias/mexico/legisladora-del-pes-da-positivo-de-covid-19-ya-son-3-diputados/ar-BB11T7rR PES legislator tests positive for Covid-19; now there are 3 deputies] {{in lang|es}} La Jornada, 29 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Jaime Ruiz Sacrist\u00e1n, businessperson (CEO [[Mexican Stock Exchange]])<ref name=univision>[https://www.univision.com/radio/radio-nacional/el-covid-19-no-perdona-camila-sodi-y-otros-famosos-mexicanos-afectados-por-el-coronavirus-fotos \ud83d\udcf8 COVID-19 does not forgive: Camila Sodi and other famous Mexicans affected by the coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} by Constaninos Papilias, Univision, 20 Mar 2020, retrieved 29 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Odalys Ram\u00edrez, television presenter and model (''\u00a1Cu\u00e9ntamelo ya!'' and ''Al aire''; Televisa)<ref name=famous />\n*[[Camila Sodi]], 33, singer and actress<ref name=famous />\n{{End div col}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Div col}}\n*[[2020 in Mexico]]\n*[[2020s]]\n*[[Fourth Transformation]]\n*[[History of smallpox in Mexico]]\n*[[Cocoliztli epidemics]]\n*[[Spanish flu|1918 Spanish flu pandemic]]\n*[[2009 flu pandemic in Mexico]]\n*[[HIV/AIDS in Latin America]]\n*[[Dengue fever outbreaks]]\n*[[Epidemiology of chikungunya|2014 chikungunya outbreak in Mexico]]\n*[[2015\u20132016 Zika virus epidemic]]\n{{End div col}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Mexico]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in North America|Mexico]]\n[[Category:2020 in Mexico|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Mexico]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Mexico]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in Mexico]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Mexico]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Impacts of the coronavirus in Mexico}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mexico\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Mexico.svg\n| legend1         = Map of the outbreak in Mexico (as of 29 March)\n{{legend|#FCEED3|Confirmed 1~5}}\n{{legend|#F2A88D|Confirmed 6~10}}\n{{legend|#E36654|Confirmed 11~20}}\n{{legend|#E5354B|Confirmed 21~50}}\n{{legend|#87353F|Confirmed 51~200}}\n{{legend|#630606|Confirmed 201~500}}\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Mexico]]\n| first_case      = [[Mexico City]] and [[Los Mochis]]<ref name=\"First\" />\n| arrival_date    = 28 February 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=02|day1=28|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China<br /> (via Italy and the United States)<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Confirman-siete-casos-de-coronavirus-en-Mexico-20200307-0085.html |title= Confirman siete casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |language=Spanish |work=informador.mx |date=7 March 2020 |access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n| recovery_cases  = 634<ref name=\"youtube1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=urlavWn2FWw&feature=youtu.be&t=675 |title=#ConferenciaDePrensa: #Coronavirus #COVID19 #Qu\u00e9dateEnCasaYa &#124; 1\u00b0 de abril de 2020 |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 79\n| confirmed_cases = 1890\n| suspected_cases = 4653\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = https://coronavirus.gob.mx/\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Mexico]] in February 2020. As of 4 April, there had been 1890 cases of COVID-19 in Mexico and 79 reported deaths.<ref name=\"3april\" />\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Mexico medical cases chart}}\n\n=== January 2020 ===\nOn 22 January 2020, the [[Secretariat of Health (Mexico)|Secretariat of Health]] issued a statement saying that the novel coronavirus COVID-19 did not present a danger to Mexico. 441 cases have been confirmed in [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in mainland China|China]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Thailand|Thailand]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Korea|South Korea]], and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|the United States]], and a travel advisory was issued on 9 January.<ref name=indigo />\n\nOn January 30, 2020 before the declaration of a pandemic by the [[World Health Organization]] the Government of Mexico designed a ''Preparation and Response Plan'' that was made by the National Committee for Health Safety, a working group led by Secretariat of Health composed by different health entities aiming to act upon the imminent arrival of the pandemic. This group carried out a series of alert measures, rehabilitation and updating of epidemiological regulations based on the International Health Regulations, being the first Latam country that deployed a [[mathematical modelling of infectious disease]].<ref name=salud />\n\n=== February 2020 ===\nThe cruise ship ''[[Grand Princess]]'' docked in [[Puerto Vallarta]] (15 February), [[Manzanillo, Colima|Manzanillo]] (16 February), [[Mazatl\u00e1n]] (17 February) and [[Cabo San Lucas]](18 February), spending 9 to 12 hours in each port. The first COVID-19 death in California was a man who had been on this ship on an earlier cruise. This ship was later quarantined off San Francisco and docked in Oakland 11 March with 21 onboard who tested positive for the coronavirus.<ref>[https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-03-09/what-we-know-about-grand-princess-docking-coronavirus-quarantine What we know about Grand Princess docking] Los Angeles Times</ref>\n\nThe cruise ship {{ship||MSC Meraviglia}}, which was not allowed to dock in the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Cayman Islands|Cayman Islands]] or [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Jamaica|Jamaica]], docked in [[Cozumel]], Quintana Roo, on 27 February. Three passengers were diagnosed with ''[[influenza A virus]],'' but no cases of coronavirus were found.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://politica.expansion.mx/mexico/2020/02/26/el-crucero-que-arribo-a-cozumel-esta-libre-de-coronavirus |title=El crucero que arrib\u00f3 a Cozumel est\u00e1 libre de coronavirus |trans-title=The cruise ship that arrived in Cozumel is free of coronaviruses |language=es |work=Expansi\u00f3n Politica |date=27 February 2020 |access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, Mexico confirmed its first three cases. A 35-year-old man and a 59-year-old man in [[Mexico City]] and a 41-year-old man in the northern state of [[Sinaloa]] tested positive and were held in isolation at a hospital and a hotel, respectively. They had travelled to [[Bergamo]] and stayed in Italy for a week in mid-February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2020/02/28/mexico-confirms-its-first-2-coronavirus-cases/|title=Mexico Confirms Its First 2 Coronavirus Cases|last=|first=|date=28 February 2020|website=CBS Los Angeles |url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20200228134645-auoh9/|title=Mexico confirms first coronavirus cases in two men returned from Italy|last=Foundation|first=Thomson Reuters|website=news.trust.org|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"First\">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/GobiernoMX/status/1233418133353844736|title=La @SSalud_mx confirm\u00f3 dos casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico, el primero en la capital y el segundo en Sinaloa. Se trata de pacientes de bajo riesgo que est\u00e1n siendo atendidos. Invitamos a la poblaci\u00f3n a seguir informada y tomar medidas de prevenci\u00f3n|last=M\u00e9xico|first=Gobierno de|date=28 February 2020|website=@GobiernoMX|language=es|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/van-3-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico|title=Van 3 casos confirmados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico|website=El Financiero|language=es|access-date=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 February, a fourth case was detected and confirmed in the city of [[Torre\u00f3n]], in the state of [[Coahuila]], from a 20-year-old woman who traveled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.milenio.com/estados/coronavirus-torreon-confirma-miguel-riquelme-caso-covid19|title=Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: lo \u00faltimo del nuevo caso en Torre\u00f3n|website=www.milenio.com|accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== March 2020 ===\n====March 1 to 15====\nOn 1 March, a fifth case was announced in [[Chiapas]] in a student who had just returned from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnoticias.mx/confirman-caso-de-coronavirus-en-chiapas/159656|title=Confirman caso de coronavirus en Chiapas|website=ABC Noticias|language=es|date=1 March 2020|accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref> On 6 March, a sixth case was confirmed in the [[State of Mexico]] in a 71-year-old man who had returned from Italy on 21 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://politica.expansion.mx/mexico/2020/03/06/confirman-sexto-caso-de-coronavirus-en-el-estado-de-mexico|title=La Secretar\u00eda de Salud confirma el sexto caso de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico|date=7 March 2020|website=ADNPol\u00edtico|accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nCOVID-19 was the topic of conversation at the meeting of the National Governors' Conference (Conago) held on 5 March 2020. In addition to governors from different states (or state health representatives), the directors of [[Instituto de Salud para el Bienestar|Instituto de Salud para el Bienestar (INSABI)]], [[Mexican Social Security Institute|IMSS]], and [[Institute for Social Security and Services for State Workers|ISSSTE]] participated.<ref name=conago>[https://www.elsoldecuernavaca.com.mx/local/analizan-gobernadores-situacion-del-coronavirus-4928720.html Governors analyze the situation of Coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} by Miriam Estrada, ''El Sol de Cuernavaca'', 5 Mar 2020, retrieved 16 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nOn March 6 during the first session of National Council of Health, [[Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell Ram\u00edrez]], one of the main strategists and spokespersons of Mexican Government on pandemics, led the first daily press conference on Covid-19.<ref name=nat_coun_health>{{Citation|title=Conferencia de prensa. Informe diario sobre coronavirus COVID-19 en M\u00e9xico. Secretar\u00eda de Salud|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZruOELSa7vA|language=en|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 March, a seventh case was also confirmed in [[Mexico City]] in a 46-year-old male who had previously had contact with another confirmed case in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reporteindigo.com/reporte/confirman-el-septimo-caso-de-coronavirus-en-mexico/|title=Se eleva a 7 el n\u00famero de casos confirmados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico|accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 March, an eighth case was reported in [[Puebla (state)|Puebla]], a 47-year-old German man who had returned from a business trip to Italy.<ref name=\"8 cases\">{{cite web |first1=|title=Puebla reporta primer caso positivo de coronavirus |url=https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/proveedor-aleman-de-volkswagen-dio-positivo-a-coronavirus-secretaria-de-salud-de-puebla |website=El Financiero |publisher=Cuartoscuro |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> On the same date, 40 members of a dance company in Puebla, returning from a tour in Italy, were quarantined.<ref name=\"Ballet Ce Acatl\">{{cite web |last1=Arellano Garc\u00eda |first1=Cesar |title=Supervisar\u00e1n salud de ballet folkl\u00f3rico que vuelve de Italia |url=https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/10/supervisaran-salud-de-ballet-folklorico-que-vuelve-de-italia-4751.html |website=La Jornada |publisher=La Jornada |accessdate=11 March 2020|date=10 March 2020 }}</ref> The [[Mexican Stock Exchange]] fell to a record low on 10 March due to fears of the coronavirus and because of falling oil prices. The [[Bank of Mexico|Bank of Mexico (Banxico)]] stepped in to prop up the value of the peso, which fell 14% to 22.929 per US dollar.<ref name=banixco>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexicos-stock-market-hits-record-low-over-coronavirus-crisis-and-collapsing-oil-prices Mexico's stock market hits record low over coronavirus crisis and collapsing oil prices] {{in lang|en}} ''El Universal'' (English), 10 March 2020</ref>\n\nOn 11 March, a ninth case was confirmed in the city of [[Monterrey]], [[Nuevo Le\u00f3n]]. A 57-year-old man, who had recently come back from a trip all across Europe, was placed under quarantine. The man, who has remained anonymous, came back from his trip a week before and had contact with eight other people who have also been placed under quarantine in their houses. The man has been confirmed to reside in the city of [[San Pedro Garza Garc\u00eda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mty.telediario.mx/local/confirman-el-primer-caso-de-coronavirus-en-nuevo-leon|title=Confirman el primer caso de coronavirus en Nuevo Le\u00f3n|date=11 March 2020|website=Telediario Monterrey|language=es|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, Mexico announced it had a total of 15 confirmed cases, with new cases in [[Puebla]] and [[Durango]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.msn.com/es-mx/noticias/mexico/ya-son-15-casos-de-coronavirus-en-m%C3%A9xico-hay-82-sospechosos/ar-BB117yPi?ocid=msedgntp|title=Ya son 15 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 82 sospechosos|website=www.msn.com|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> A day later, senator {{ill|Samuel Garc\u00eda Sep\u00falveda|es}} accused the federal government of hiding the true number of confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sdpnoticias.com/local/nuevo-leon/gobierno-de-mexico-esconde-cifras-coronavirus-pandemia-samuel-garcia.html |title=Gobierno de M\u00e9xico ESCONDE cifras reales de CORONAVIRUS, acusa Samuel Garc\u00eda|last=SDPnoticias.com|website=SDPnoticias.com |language=spanish|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> After that, the government of Nuevo Le\u00f3n declared Phase 2. Mexico on 13 March had confirmed a total of 16 cases.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nOn 13 March, it was confirmed that the [[Mexican Stock Exchange]] Chairman, Jaime Ruiz Sacristan, tested positive as an asymptomatic case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/da-positivo-de-coronavirus-el-presidente-de-la-bolsa-mexicana-jaime-ruiz-sacristan|title=Da positivo de coronavirus el presidente de la Bolsa Mexicana, Jaime Ruiz Sacrist\u00e1n|website=El Financiero|language=es|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> Later, the Secretariat of Health announced in press conference that the number of confirmed cases had risen to 26.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Espino |first1=Manuel |title=M\u00e9xico suma 26 casos positivos de coronavirus |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-13-de-marzo-mexico-suma-26-casos-positivos-de-coronavirus |website=El Universal |date=14 March 2020 |publisher=El Universal, compa\u00f1\u00eda period\u00edstica Nacional |accessdate=14 March 2020 |ref=13 March 26 cases}}</ref> Several universities, including the [[National Autonomous University of Mexico|UNAM]] and [[Monterrey Institute of Technology and Higher Education|Tec de Monterrey]], switched to virtual classes. Authorities announced to be considering the cancellation of the ''Festival Internacional de Cine de Guadalajara''. In M\u00e9rida, the ''Tianguis Tur\u00edstico'' was postponed to September. Several major sporting events were also canceled.<ref name=cancelations>{{cite web |url=https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Suspenden-actividades-masivas-por-coronavirus-20200313-0020.html |title=Suspenden actividades masivas por coronavirus |trans-title=Massive Suspension of Activities Due to Coronavirus |language=Spanish |work=Informador.mx |date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Jos\u00e9 Alfonso Su\u00e1rez del Real y Aguilera entregando gel antibacterial.jpg|thumb|On 14 March 2020 sport events such as female football matches were open to public. At Estadio Ol\u00edmpico Universitario, authorities were pouring hand sanitizer at the entrance.]]\nOn 14 March, Fernando Petersen, the secretary of health of the state of [[Jalisco]], confirmed the first two cases of COVID-19 were detected in Hospital Civil de [[Guadalajara]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.informador.mx/jalisco/Confirman-primeros-dos-casos-de-coronavirus-en-Jalisco-20200314-0052.html|title=Confirman primeros dos casos de coronavirus en Jalisco|website=El Informador: Noticias de Jalisco, M\u00e9xico, Deportes & Entretenimiento|language=es-ES|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> Two new cases were confirmed in Nuevo Le\u00f3n, and the [[Secretariat of Public Education (Mexico)|Secretariat of Public Education (SEP)]] announced that all sporting and civic events in schools would be canceled.<ref name=sep>{{cite web |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-sep-cancela-eventos-deportivos-y-civicos-en-escuelas |title=SEP cancela eventos deportivos y c\u00edvicos en escuelas por coronavirus |trans-title=SEP cancels sporting and civic events in schools due to coronavirus |language=Spanish |work=El Universal |date=14 March 2020}}</ref> The same day, the Secretariat of Education announced that Easter break, originally planned from 6 to 17 April, would be extended from 20 March to 20 April as a preventive measure.<ref name=\"Prevention Easter break in schools\">{{cite web |last1=Huizache |first1=Dolores |title=SEP anuncia que vacaciones de Semana Santa se adelantan por coronavirus |url=https://www.am.com.mx/noticias/SEP-anuncia-que-vacaciones-de-Semana-Santa-se-adelantan-por-coronavirus-20200314-0021.html |website=AM Mexico |publisher=EDITORIAL MARTINICA S.A. DE C.V. |accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Secretariat of Finance and Public Credit|Secretariat of Finance and Public Credit (SCHP)]] announced it was taking measures to prevent a 0.5% fall in [[Gross domestic product |gross domestic product (GDP)]].<ref name=schp>{{cite web |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/cartera/listo-paquete-contraciclico-para-impulsar-economia |title=Por Covid-19, Hacienda tiene plan contrac\u00edclico |trans-title=Because of coronavirus, Treasury has a countercyclical package ready to boost economy |work=El Universal |date=14 March 2020 |access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref> Drugstores in [[Cuernavaca]] report shortages of masks, antibacterial gel, and other items.<ref>[https://www.elsoldecuernavaca.com.mx/local/comienzan-a-escasear-productos-por-covid-19-4971890.html Products start to be scarce due to COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} Jessica Arellano, ''El Sol de Cuernavaca'', 14 Mar 2020</ref> On the same day the [[Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de Nuevo Le\u00f3n|Autonomous University of Nuevo Leon, (UANL)]] (the country's third largest university in terms of student population) suspended classes for its more than 206,000 students starting on March 17 and ending on April 20.<ref name=uanl>{{cite web |last1=Garza|first1=Aracely|title= Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de NL suspende clases por Covid-19|language=es|trans-title=Autonomous University of NL suspends classes because of Covid-19|url= https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/universidad-autonoma-de-nl-suspende-clases-por-covid-19/1369792 |website=Exc\u00e9lsior |date=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Garza|first1=Aracely|language=es|title= Suspende UANL clases virtuales |url= https://m.imagenradio.com.mx/suspende-uanl-clases-virtuales |website=Imagen Radio |date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nBusinessman Jos\u00e9 Kuri was reported in critical condition on 14 March after a trip to [[Vail, Colorado]], United States, although early reports of his death were false.<ref>{{cite web|website=El Sol de M\u00e9xico|title=El empresario Jos\u00e9 Kuri se encuentra en estado cr\u00edtico a causa de coronavirus|trans-title=The businessman Jos\u00e9 Kuri is in critical condition due to coronavirus|language=es|date=15 Mar 2020|accessdate=16 Mar 2020|author=EFE|url=https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/mexico/sociedad/el-empresario-jose-kuri-se-encuentra-en-estado-critico-a-causa-de-coronavirus-4974999.html}}</ref> As of 14 March, there have been 41 confirmed cases of [[COVID-19]] in Mexico.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://politica.expansion.mx/presidencia/2020/03/14/mexico-llega-a-41-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-con-155-sospechosos |title=M\u00e9xico llega a 41 casos confirmados de coronavirus, con 155 casos sospechosos |work=expansion.mx |language=Spanish |date=14 March 2020 |access-date=16 March 2020|trans-title=Mexico has 41 confirmed and 155 suspected cases of coronavirus}}</ref>\n\nThe 14 and 15 March ''Festival Vive Latino'' (rock and Latin music) in Mexico City opened according to schedule, in spite of fears of contagion. Temperatures of the 70,000 people who attend each day were taken at the door and anti-bacterial gel was widely distributed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/14/el-coronavirus-avanza-apresurado-en-mexico-y-las-pruebas-de-detencion-cuestan-hasta-18000-pesos/ |title=El coronavirus avanza apresurado en M\u00e9xico y las pruebas de detecci\u00f3n cuestan hasta 18,000 pesos |trans-title=Coronavirus rushes ahead in Mexico and screening tests cost up to 18,000 pesos |language=Spanish |work=Infobae |date=14 March 2020 |access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref> Organizers said that the ''[[Passion Play of Iztapalapa]]'' would continue as scheduled in Holy Week. Tito Dom\u00ednguez, vice president of the organizing committee, noted that a miracle had saved Iztapalapa during the [[Cholera outbreaks and pandemics|cholera outbreak in 1833]].<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/pasion-de-cristo-en-iztapalapa-podria-cancelarse-debido-al-covid-19-coronavirus-claudia-sheinbaum-iglesia-catolica-pasion-de-cristo-coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-4974131.html Coronavirus will not stop the Stations of the Cross in Iztapalapa: organizing committee] {{in lang|es}} Maleny Navarro, ''El Sol de M\u00e9xico''. 15 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, Head of Government [[Claudia Sheinbaum]] stated that Mexico City expects to spend an extra MXN $100 million (US$4.4 million) to prevent the spread of COVID-19.<ref name=sheinbaum>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/preven-gasto-de-100-mdp-extra-para-combatir-coronavirus-en-cdmx-4974203.html Expenditure of 100 extra mp to prevent coronavirus in CDMX] {{in lang|es}} by Maleny Navarro, ''El Sol de M\u00e9xico'', 15 Mar 2020</ref> The first confirmed case of coronavirus in [[Acapulco]], Guerrero, was reported.<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/republica/sociedad/confirman-primer-caso-de-covid-19-en-guerrero-coronavirus-4974870.html Confirman primer caso de Covid-19 en Guerrero] {{in lang|es}} by Jos\u00e9 Francisco Zorroza, ''El Sol de Acapulco'', 15 Mar 2020</ref> [[Quer\u00e9taro]] reported two new cases, bringing the total to six.<ref>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/mundo/coronavirus-covid-19/nota/1932576/0/aumenta-seis-el-numero-de-casos-de-coronavirus-en-queretaro#info Queretaro increases the number of coronavirus cases to six] {{in lang|es}} by Francisco Floes Hernndez, El Universal, 15 Mar 2020</ref> [[Nuevo Leon]] reported its fifth case.<ref>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-suman-5-casos-positivos-en-nuevo-leon Coronavirus: 5 positive cases in Nuevo Leon] {{in lang|es}} by David Carrizales, 15 Mar 2020</ref> The [[Norte\u00f1o (music)|Norte\u00f1o]] group Los Tres Tristes Tigres released a [[corrido|song]] on 15 March titled \"El corrido del coronavirus\".<ref>[https://www.elsoldecuernavaca.com.mx/doble-via/virales/video-el-pin-coronavirus-a-todos-saco-de-quicio-el-nuevo-corrido-de-los-los-tres-tristes-tigres-covid19-covid-19-salud-humor-canciones-musica-nortea-comparas-de-panico-papel-de-bano-tom-hanks-amlo-disneyland-viral-corrido-4974778.html Los Tres Tristes Tigres compose \"El corrido del coronavirus\"] {{in lang|es}} by Miguel Ceballos, ''El Sol de Puebla'', 15 Mar 2020</ref>\n\n====March 16 to 22====\n[[File: Panic buying in mexico due to covid19.jpg |thumbnail|right|Panic buying of toilet paper at a [[Soriana]] supermarket in [[Ensenada, Baja California]] due to the COVID-19 pandemic.]]\nAs of 16 March, President L\u00f3pez Obrador continued to downplay the impact of coronavirus. \"Pandemics ... won't do anything to us,\" and accused the press and the opposition for its reportage.<ref>[https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2020-03-19/as-mexican-peso-collapses-over-coronavirus-threat-criticism-falls-on-president-lopez-obrador \"As Mexican peso collapses over coronavirus threat, criticism falls on president Lopez Obrador\" Los Angeles Times 2020/03/20] accessed 20 March 2020</ref>  On 16 March, lawyer Marco Antonio del Toro petitioned the federal courts to cease all but essential activities for a period of 30 to 40 days because of the coronavirus outbreak.<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/mexico/piden-suspender-actividades-en-juzgados-y-tribunales-por-coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-contagios-pandemia-epidemia-4976721.html Suspension of judicial activities for coronavirus requested] {{in lang|es}} Manrique Gandaria, ''El Sol de M\u00e9xico'', 16 Mar 2020</ref> The total of confirmed cases reached 82.<ref name=\"Marc 16 confirmed cases\">{{cite web |last1=Castillo Torres |first1=Gustavo |title=Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: 82 casos confirmados; s\u00f3lo 2% est\u00e1n graves |url=https://www.unotv.com/noticias/portal/nacional/detalle/coronavirus-mexico-82-casos-confirmados-solo-2-estan-graves-785052/ |website=UnoTV |date=17 March 2020 |publisher=AMX Contenido S.A. de C.V. |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Universidad Aut\u00f3noma del Estado de Morelos|Autonomous University of the State of Morelos, (UAEM)]] suspended classes for its 22,000 students.<ref name=uaem>[https://www.milenio.com/estados/uaem-suspende-clases-por-coronavirus UAEM suspends classes due to coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} by David Monroy, ''Milenio'', 16 Mar 2020</ref> A diplomatic incident arose between the governments of Mexico and [[El Salvador]], concerning 12 Salvadorean citizens wearing face masks on a plane departing from Mexico City to San Salvador. [[Nayib Bukele]], president of El Salvador denounced as \"irresponsible\" that they were allowed to board the plane along with other passengers and offered to send a plane to transport them without contact with other people. The claim was supported by [[Avianca]] airline<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/AviancaCAM/status/1239696214469337088|title=Agradecemos al Presidente del El Salvador @nayibbukele por darnos la informaci\u00f3n y alertarnos sobre los pacientes con COVID-19 intentando abordar el vuelo de Avianca #431 proveniente de la Ciudad de M\u00e9xico hacia El Salvador el d\u00eda 16 de Marzo de 2020.|last=Centroam\u00e9rica|first=Avianca|date=2020-03-16|website=@AviancaCAM|language=es|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> while the Mexican government said that there were no reasons to assume that they were positive for COVID-19. Eventually, the flight was cancelled. [[Marcelo Ebrard]], head of Foreign Affairs announced after negative results of COVID tests of that Salvadorean passengers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.milenio.com/politica/coronavirus-llama-ebrard-nayib-bukele-aclarar-fuentes-pasajeros|title=Coronavirus: llama Ebrard a Nayib Bukele aclarar fuentes de pasajeros|website=www.milenio.com|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, 11 new cases were confirmed, raising the national total to 93, with [[Campeche]] being the only state with no confirmed cases.<ref name=\"Confirmed cases 17 March\">{{cite web |last1=Milenio Digital |title=Secretar\u00eda de Salud reporta 93 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 206 sospechosos |url=https://www.milenio.com/politica/coronavirus-mexico-93-casos-confirmados-206-sospechosos |website=Milenio.com |publisher=Milenio Diario, S.A de C.V |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> Mexico's limited response, including allowing a large concert and the women's soccer championship, as well as a lack of testing, have been criticized. Critics note that president [[Andr\u00e9s Manuel L\u00f3pez Obrador|L\u00f3pez Obrador]] does not practice social distancing but continues to greet large crowds, and the borders have not been closed. Of particular concern is the health of thousands of migrants in temporary camps along the border with the United States. The former national commissioner for influenza in Mexico during the [[2009 flu pandemic]], Alejandro Mac\u00edas, said the problem is compounded by the fact that Mexico lacks sufficient intensive care unit beds, medical care workers and ventilators.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/mexico-government-pressure-coronavirus-response-200316210710906.html Mexico's government under pressure over coronavirus response] by Jihan Abdalla, Al Jazeera, 17 March 2020  [https://thehill.com/latino/488100-mexico-under-international-criticism-for-coronavirus-response Mexico under international criticism for coronavirus response] BY RAFAEL BERNAL, The Hill, 18 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, 25 more cases were confirmed raising the total to 118 cases and 314 suspected cases.<ref name=\"18march\">{{cite web |url=https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-mexico-casos-confirmados-positivos-covid19-hoy-miercoles-18-marzo-secretaria-salud/|title= Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: Hay 118 casos confirmados de COVID-19|date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.milenio.com/politica/coronavirus-mexico-118-casos-confirmados-314-sospechosos |title= Confirman 118 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 314 sospechosos |date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=Milenio}}</ref> Authorities in Jalisco are concerned about a group of 400 people who recently returned from [[Vail, Colorado]]; 40 people have symptoms of COVID-19.<ref>[https://www.milenio.com/internacional/coronavirus-mexico-18-marzo-noticias-hora-casos-vivo Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico, noticias de \u00faltima hora] Milenio, 18 Mar 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2020-03-20/some-of-mexicos-wealthiest-residents-went-to-colorado-to-ski-they-brought-home-coronavirus \"Some of Mexico's Wealthiest Residents Went to Colorado to Ski and Brought Home Coronavirus\". Los Angeles Times 2020/03/20] accessed 20 March 2020.</ref> The same day, the Mexican government announced that they will allocate 3.5 billion pesos ({{abbr|approx.|approximately}} 146 million US dollars{{refn|on March 18}}) to buy medical and laboratory equipment, washing and disinfection material, and ventilators.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-18-de-marzo-aumentan-118-los-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico |title= AUMENTAN A 118 LOS CASOS CONFIRMADOS DE CORONAVIRUS EN M\u00c9XICO |date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=El Universal}}</ref> During the night  the first COVID-19 related death in the country was confirmed, a 41-year-old man without a travel history outside the country who was hospitalized at the National Institute of Respiratory Diseases (INER).<ref name=\"death1\">{{cite web|url= https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/18/fallece-victima-de-covid-19-en-el-iner-9638.html |title= Fallece primera v\u00edctima de Covid-19 en el INER |date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=[[La Jornada]]}}</ref> Colima Governor [[Jos\u00e9 Ignacio Peralta]] declared a state of emergency after the state's first case, a man who had recently returned from Germany, was reported on 17 March.<ref>[https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Colima-declara-emergencia-por-COVID-19-20200318-0134.html Colima declara emergencia por COVID-19] El Informador, 18 Mar 2020</ref> [[Ford Motor Company|Ford]], [[Honda]], and [[Audi]] closed their manufacturing plants in Mexico.<ref name=ford>{{cite news|author=<!-- not stated -->|title=Empresas automotrices suspenden producci\u00f3n en M\u00e9xico|language=es |url=https://www.informador.mx/economia/Empresas-automotrices-suspenden-produccion-en-Mexico-20200318-0114.html|website=El Informador|date=March 18, 2020|access-date=March 19, 2020}}</ref> Hundreds of hotel employees in [[Canc\u00fan]] were fired.<ref name=cancun>[https://laverdadnoticias.com/quintanaroo/Coronavirus-Cancun-Comenzaron-los-despidos-en-los-hoteles-20200318-0006.html Coronavirus Canc\u00fan: Comenzaron los despidos en los hoteles] {{in lang|es}} by Angel Bal\u00e1n, La Verdad, 18 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nAuthorities announced on 18 March that they were looking for hundreds of citizens who may be carriers of the coronavirus, especially in the states of Puebla, Jalisco, Aguascalientes, and Guerrero. A four-member family in Puebla who had traveled to the United States kept their symptoms secret as they visited neighbors in La Vista and visited a gym. Authorities were still trying to track down the 400 people in Jalisco and Nayarit who recently traveled to Vail, Colorado. In Aguascalientes they were looking to track down passengers of Fight 2638 who traveled with a sick man from New York. The [[Autonomous University of Guerrero|Autonomous University of Guerrero (UAGRO)]] in Chilpancingo closed after a female student tested positive for the virus. The Technical Institute of Guerrero and the state Supreme Court also closed.<ref name=look>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexican-authorities-are-tracking-hundreds-possible-covid-19-carriers Mexican authorities are tracking hundreds of possible Covid 19 carriers] {{in lang|en}} by David Carrizales, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n\n[[Morelos]] had its first two confirmed cases on 19 March\u2014a 54-year-old woman from [[Cuautla, Morelos|Cuautla]] and a 37-year-old man from [[Cuernavaca]].<ref>[https://www.diariodemorelos.com/noticias/urgente-confirmados-ya-2-casos-de-coronavirus-en-morelos URGENTE: CONFIRMADOS YA 2 CASOS DE CORONAVIRUS COVID19 EN MORELOS] {{in lang|es}} ''Diario de Morelos'', 19 Mar 2020</ref> [[Sinaloa]] announced its third case, a 20-year-old woman from [[Culiac\u00e1n]].<ref>[https://www.debate.com.mx/culiacan/Confirman-el-tercer-caso-de-coronavirus-en-Sinaloa-20200319-0157.html Confirman el tercer caso de coronavirus en Sinaloa] {{in lang|es}} by FRANCISCO CASTRO, ''Debate'', 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nU.S Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]] announced on 20 March there would be restrictions on travel across the [[Mexico\u2013United States border]]. Said restrictions would not apply to cargo.<ref name=pompeo>{{cite web|website=Deadline|title=President Donald Trump Goes Off On NBC News Reporter, Comcast During Coronavirus Press Briefing|date=March 20, 2020|author=Ted Johnson|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/u-s-and-mexico-to-restrict-non-essential-travel-on-southern-border-mike-pompeo-warns-of-disinformation-1202888618/|language=en}}</ref> The [[Instituto Nacional de Antropolog\u00eda e Historia|National Institute of Anthropology and History (INAH)]] announced that the archaeological zones [[Teotihuac\u00e1n]], [[Xochicalco]], and [[El Tepozteco]] will be closed on 21\u201322 March. [[Chich\u00e9n Itz\u00e1]] will close indefinitely starting 21 March. [[Guachimontones]] will close 21, 22, and 23 March. [[Palenque]], [[Tula (Mesoamerican site)|Tula]] and [[Tingambato]] will close 21 March.<ref name=inah>[https://launion.com.mx/morelos/zona-sur/noticias/157226-cerraran-las-zonas-arqueologicas-de-xochicalco-y-tepoztlan.html?utm_medium=Social&utm_source=Facebook&fbclid=IwAR3J791dkyCGjqbxVpYJPQhZ2i6AJi6PvA9ylt65t0LS1hN20dxAET1jjoA#Echobox=1584718003 Cerrar\u00e1n las zonas arqueol\u00f3gicas de Xochicalco y Tepoztl\u00e1n] {{in lang|es}} La Union de Morelos, 20 Mar 2020</ref> [[Alsea (company)|Alsea]], which operates restaurants such as Starbucks, VIPS, and Domino's Pizza offered its employees unpaid leave.<ref name=alsea>[https://www.diariodemorelos.com/noticias/starbucks-y-vips-ofrecen-empleados-dejar-de-trabajar-un-mes-sin-goce-de-sueldo-por-covid-19?fbclid=IwAR1bHSJdt5O5D8QECH-3Yk547e2nKDlW-eZtwO870EFtZHBUAlkQOjOjr4s Starbucks y VIPs ofrecen a empleados dejar de trabajar un mes sin goce de sueldo, por COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} El Diario de Morelos, 20 Mar 2020</ref> Mayor Juanita Romero (PAN) of [[Nacozari de Garc\u00eda Municipality]], Sonora, declares a curfew, in effect until 20 April. Only the [[President of Mexico]] has the legal authority to declare such a declaration.<ref name=curfew>[https://www.proceso.com.mx/622668/nacozari-toque-de-queda Alcaldesa de Nacozari ordena toque de queda, facultad exclusiva del presidente] {{in lang|es}} by Milton Martinez, Proceso, 20 Mar 2020</ref> During the night, 38 more cases and one more death were confirmed raising the total to 203 cases, 2 deaths, and 606 suspected cases.<ref name=\"20march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/seguridad/coronavirus-20-de-marzo-mexico-confirma-dos-muertos-por-covid-19-suma-203-casos |title= M\u00c9XICO CONFIRMA DOS MUERTOS POR CORONAVIRUS; SUMA 203 CASOS POSITIVOS |date=March 20, 2020|language=es|work=El Universal |author1= Alexis Ortiz |author2= Perla Miranda }}</ref>\n\nOn March 21 the total confirmed cases were 251.<ref name=\"21march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/sube-a-251-el-numero-de-contagiados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico/1371282 |title= Sube a 251 el n\u00famero de contagiados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |date=March 21, 2020|language=es|work=Exc\u00e9lsior |author1= Redacci\u00f3n}}</ref> One day later 65 more cases were confirmed and the total of suspected cases grew to 793.<ref name=\"22march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eleconomista.com.mx/politica/Cifra-de-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-Mexico-sube-a-316-Secretaria-de-Salud-20200322-0050.html |title= Con 316 casos confirmados, sigue fase de transici\u00f3n |date=March 22, 2020|language=es|work=El Economista |author1= Rolando Ramos}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, bars, nightclubs, movie theaters, and museums were closed in Mexico City.<ref name=bars>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexico-city-closes-museums-bars-nightclubs-and-movie-theaters-bid-halt-coronavirus-spread Mexico City closes museums, bars, nightclubs, and movie theaters in a bid to halt coronavirus spread] {{in lang|en}} El Universal, 23 March 2020</ref> Governor [[Enrique Alfaro Ram\u00edrez]] of Jalisco announced that beginning Thursday, 26 March, Jalisco and seven other states in the [[Baj\u00edo]] and western Mexico will block flights from areas such as [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in California|California]] that have a high rate of coronavirus. He also said that they will purchase 25,000 testing kits.<ref name=planes>[https://www.debate.com.mx/guadalajara/Jalisco-bloquearia-vuelos-y-compra-25-mil-pruebas-de-COVID-19-20200323-0224.html Jalisco will block flights and buy 25 thousand tests of COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} by CAROLINA SOL\u00cdS, Debate, 23 March</ref>\n\n====March 23 to 31====\n[[File:Acceso de personas con s\u00edntomas de enfermedades respiratorias al Instituto Nacional de Ciencias M\u00e9dicas y Nutrici\u00f3n Salvador Zubir\u00e1n.jpg|thumbnail|right|People entering to a specially respiratory illness symptom assessment area at the [[Salvador Zubir\u00e1n National Institute of Health Sciences and Nutrition|Instituto Nacional de Ciencias M\u00e9dicas y Nutrici\u00f3n Salvador Zubir\u00e1n]], Mexico City, Mexico. The hospital was converted into a special care area for COVID patients.]]\n\nMexico entered Phase 2 of the coronavirus pandemic on 23 March 2020, according to the [[World Health Organization]], with 367 confirmed cases. Phase 2 includes cases where the sick individuals did not have direct contact with someone who had recently been in another country.<ref name=who>[https://www.forbes.com.mx/noticias-salud-mexico-fase-2-pandemia-por-coronavirus-oms/?utm_source=nora-push&utm_medium=push-notifications&utm_campaign=new-nora-push M\u00e9xico, en Fase 2 de pandemia por Coronavirus: OMS] Forbes Mexico, 23 Mar 2020</ref> On the same day it was confirmed that two more people died from COVID-19, raising the total to 4 reported deaths.<ref name=\"23march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.sdpnoticias.com/nacional/muertos-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico-cifras-23-de-marzo.html |title= Suman 4 muertos por Covid-19 en M\u00e9xico; confirman 367 casos de contagio |date=March 23, 2020|language=es|work=SDP Noticias |author1= Alexis Pav\u00f3n}}</ref> That day was announced on President L\u00f3pez Obrador's daily press conference the realization of the National Campaign of Healthy Distancing ({{ill|Jornada Nacional de Sana Distancia|lt=|es||WD=}}) a national program of non-pharmaceutical measures based on [[social distancing]] among the behavioral changes suggested by WHO as hand washing, covering one's mouth when coughing, maintaining distance from other people, and monitoring and [[self-isolation]] for people who suspect they are infected.<ref name=social>{{cite web |url=https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/23/comienza-la-jornada-nacional-de-sana-distancia-1056.html|title=Comienza la Jornada Nacional de Sana Distancia|last=L|first=Ang\u00e9lica Enciso|date=2020-03-23|work=[[La Jornada]]|language=es|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> On that same day in the daily press conference was announced also a media campaign led by \"Susana Distancia\" (wordplay of a healthy distance) a fictional female [[superhero]] aiming to promote social distancing into the people.<ref name=susana>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dw.com/en/mexican-superhero-susana-distancia-swoops-in-to-promote-social-distancing/a-52873960|title=Mexican superhero Susana Distancia swoops in to promote social distancing|last=Martyr|first=Kate|work=[[Deutsche Welle]]|language=en-GB|date=21 March 2020|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nMeanwhile, a [[Warren Mitofsky|Mitofsky poll]] showed that 63% of Mexicans feared contracting Covid-19 and 25.5% feared dying from it. 28% said they were not willing to stay in their homes. 38.6% believed President L\u00f3pez Obrador was handling the situation well, and 37% disapproved.<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/23/coronavirus-en-mexico-crece-el-descontento-con-el-gobierno-de-amlo-y-el-temor-al-contagio/ Coronavirus in Mexico: growing discontent with the AMLO government and fear of contagion] {{in lang|es}} Infobae, 23 Mar 2020</ref> Access to supermarkets in [[Coahuila]] was limited to one person per family, and the temperature of that person was taken before entering. The same rule applies to drugstores and convenience stores in the state, which has 12 confirmed cases of Covid-19.<ref name=supermarket>[https://mvsnoticias.com/noticias/estados/solo-una-persona-por-familia-podra-acceder-a-supermercados-en-coahuila/ Only one person per family can access supermarkets in Coahuila] {{in lang|es}} MVS Noticias, 23 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nAt his morning news conference on 24 March, President [[Andr\u00e9s Manuel L\u00f3pez Obrador|L\u00f3pez Obrador]] announced that Mexico entered Phase 2 of the coronavirus pandemic, in effect until April 30. Gatherings of more than 100 people are prohibited, and both the army and the navy will participate. The armed forces have 1,738 doctors, 1,727 nurses, 100 intensive therapy ambulances, and 400 ambulances for transportation. The military also has 5 high specialty hospitals, 36 second-level hospitals, and 272 first-level hospitals with 262 health brigades across the country. 4 deaths, 367 confirmed cases, and 826 suspected cases of COVID-19 have been reported.<ref name=amlo_phase2>[https://www.unotv.com/noticias/portal/nacional/detalle/coronavirus-en-mexico-amlo-anuncia-plan-de-proteccion-contra-covid-19-776166/?fbclid=IwAR15m1TxXEfZZiy02_RllKvYG8TWID4lW96tyjWtVqUbtO-HP12-JH0zkuQ M\u00e9xico inicia fase 2 por coronavirus; toma estas medidas] {{in lang|es}} UNO TV, 24 Mar 2020</ref> A Mexican citizen died in Peru from COVID-19. This was announced by the Foreign Ministry, which also notified that the body will be repatriated as a humanitarian operation.<ref>[https://cnnespanol.cnn.com/video/mexicano-coronavirus-contagio-muere-cusco-covid-cancilleria-relaciones-exteriores-perspectivas-mexico-cnne/ Un turista mexicano muere en Per\u00fa a causa del coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} CNN, 24 Mar 2020</ref> The first Mexican woman died from COVID-19 on March 24, raising the total to 5 reported deaths in the country.<ref name=\"death5\">{{cite web|url= https://www.radioformula.com.mx/noticias/mexico/20200324/5-muertos-por-coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-martha-mujer-hospital-angeles-hoy/| title= Muere la primera mujer por Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; van 5 decesos|author=Diego Santiago|work=Grupo F\u00f3rmula|date= March 24, 2020}}</ref> On the same day 405 total cases of COVID-19 were confirmed.<ref name=\"24march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/suman-5-decesos-por-coronavirus-en-mexico-suben-a-405-los-casos-confirmados/|title= Suman 5 decesos por coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; suben a 405 los casos confirmados |author= Redacci\u00f3n |work=El Financiero|date= March 24, 2020|language=es}}</ref> A 31-year-old male Mexican national in custody by [[U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement|U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE)]] in [[Hackensack, New Jersey]] is being held in isolation after being tested positive for Covid-19. He is the first migrant to test positive, and ICE is suspending the intake of new migrants.<ref>[https://www.fox44news.com/news/mexican-man-becomes-1st-in-immigration-detention-to-test-positive-for-covid-19/ Mexican man becomes 1st in immigration detention to test positive for COVID-19] Fox 44 News/AP, 24 Mar 2020, retrieved 26 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, Dr. Abelardo \u00c1vila, researcher at the [[Salvador Zubir\u00e1n National Institute of Health Sciences and Nutrition]] warned that Mexico was particularly vulnerable to the COVID-19 pandemic because of underlying chronic illnesses such as [[obesity]], [[diabetes]], and [[hypertension]].<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/25/mexico-es-mas-vulnerable-al-coronavirus-por-prevalencia-de-enfermedades-cronicas-dijeron-especialistas/ M\u00e9xico es m\u00e1s vulnerable al coronavirus por prevalencia de enfermedades cr\u00f3nicas, dijeron especialistas] {{in lang|es}} Infobae, 25 Mar 2020</ref> Also on 25 March President L\u00f3pez Obrador ordered the [[Mexican Air Force]] to rescue Mexicans trapped in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Argentina|Argentina]].<ref name=airforce>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/25/lopez-obrador-ordeno-a-la-fuera-aerea-trasladar-a-su-pais-a-argentinos-varados-en-mexico-por-el-coronavirus-y-repatriar-a-connacionales/ L\u00f3pez Obrador orden\u00f3 a la Fuerza A\u00e9rea una misi\u00f3n de rescate de mexicanos y argentinos varados por coronavirus]{{in lang|es}} Infobae, 25 Mar 2020</ref> In Baja California, [[PROFECO]] closed two businesses in Tijuana for price-gouging.<ref name=profecobc>[http://www.hiptex.com.mx/noticias/15232/clausura-profeco-dos-comercios-por-subir-precios-de-productos-basicos?fbclid=IwAR3HnkguUeauzsXKKErTWjURUebLIgENbS_-kqRpbfGv03ccaczAiLSRVt8 Clausura Profeco dos comercios por subir precios de productos b\u00e1sicos] Hiptex, 25 Mar 2020</ref> In Mexico City, Head of Government [[Claudia Sheinbaum]] announced financial support for families and micro industries affected by the pandemic. She also announced that automobile verification would be suspended through April 19. Movie theaters, bars, nightclubs, gyms, and other entertainment centers will remain closed.<ref name=finsupport>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/25/creditos-para-micronegocios-y-500-pesos-para-ninos-las-acciones-de-cdmx-para-apoyar-a-la-poblacion-durante-emergencia-por-coronavirus/ Cr\u00e9ditos para micronegocios y 500 pesos para ni\u00f1os: las acciones de CDMX para apoyar a la poblaci\u00f3n durante emergencia por coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} Infobae, 25 Mar 2020</ref> The same day it was reported that one man died from COVID-19 in [[San Luis Potos\u00ed]], raising the total to 6 reported deaths in Mexico and 475 confirmed cases.<ref name=\"death6\">{{cite web|author= Roc\u00edo L\u00f3pez |title= Muere hombre en San Luis Potos\u00ed por COVID-19; van 6 en M\u00e9xico|url= https://www.milenio.com/estados/coronavirus-san-luis-potosi-reportan-muerto-covid-19 |website=Milenio|date=March 25, 2020|language=es}}</ref><ref name=\"25march\">{{cite web|author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital |title= Van 6 muertes en M\u00e9xico por COVID-19; casos positivos ascienden a 475 |url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-mexico-muertes-covid19-casos-positivos-contagios-hoy-miercoles-25-marzo-2020-fase-dos-secretaria-salud/ |website=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico|date=March 25, 2020|language=es}}</ref> Governor [[Miguel Barbosa Huerta]] ([[National Regeneration Movement|Morena]]) claimed that only the wealthy were at risk, since the poor are immune to COVID-19.<ref>[https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/mexican-governor-poor-immune-coronavirus-69805644?cid=referral_taboola_feed Mexican governor says poor are 'immune' to coronavirus] AP, 26 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, President L\u00f3pez Obrador revealed he asked the [[G20]] to ensure that wealthy countries cannot take control of the world's medical supplies. He also called for assurances that borders would not be closed to commerce and that [[tariff]]s would not be unilaterally increased. Lastly, he called for an end to racism and discrimination.<ref name=g20>[https://www.tvazteca.com/aztecanoticias/politica/notas/pide-amlo-en-g-20-que-onu-controle-comercio-de-medicamentos-de-covid-19 Pide AMLO en G-20 que ONU controle comercio de medicamentos de COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} TV Azteca, 26 Mar 2020</ref> The Mexican government announced it would suspend most sectors' activities starting 26 March until 19 April, with the exception of health and energy sectors, the oil industry; and public services such as water supply, waste management and public safety.<ref name=suspend_govt>{{cite news|last=Rueda |first=Rivelino|title=A partir de hoy para gobierno actividades|url=https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/a-partir-de-hoy-para-gobierno-actividades|work=El Financiero|date=March 26, 2020|access-date=March 26, 2020|language=es}}</ref> The Secretary of Health estimated that Phase 3 of the pandemic, when the number of cases reaches its peak, will be about 19 April.<ref name=peak>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/26/escenarios-del-coronavirus-en-mexico-la-fase-3-llegara-el-19-de-abril/ Escenarios del coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: la fase 3 llegar\u00e1 el 19 de abril] {{in lang|es}} Infobae, 26 Mar 2020</ref> Protesters in [[Sonora]] insisted that the government limit border crossings with the United States.<ref name=border>[https://news.yahoo.com/mexicans-demand-crackdown-americans-crossing-154146270.html Coronavirus: Mexicans demand crackdown on Americans crossing the border] BBC, 26 Mar 2020</ref> [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]] announced that \u201cin the next few days\u201d it will start to quarantine migrants who are returned to the [[Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]] border crossing. About 65 migrants are deported from [[El Paso, Texas]] daily, about 5,200 this year.<ref name=chi>[https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/mexican-border-city-quarantine-returning-migrants-69827231?cid=clicksource_76_null_articleroll_hed Mexican border city to quarantine returning migrants] AP,26 Mar 2020</ref> Two more deaths were reported on this day; 585 cases were confirmed, and there were 2,156 suspected cases.<ref name=\"26march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.radioformula.com.mx/noticias/mexico/20200326/585-casos-coronavirus-en-mexico-salud-federal-hoy-ultimas-noticias-26-de-marzo/amp/ | title= Ya hay 585 casos confirmados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |author=Diego Santiago|work=Grupo F\u00f3rmula|date= March 26, 2020}}</ref> [[Human Rights Watch]] accused AMLO of endangering lives by not providing accurate information about the pandemic.<ref>[https://www.hrw.org/news/2020/03/26/mexico-mexicans-need-accurate-covid-19-information Mexico: Mexicans Need Accurate COVID-19 Information] Human Rights Watch, 26 March 2020</ref> The government of San Luis Potosi reported the death of a 57-year-old man on March 26, bringing the total number of deaths in the country to nine. He had hypertension and diabetes.<ref>[https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2020/03/27/tikitakas/1585280194_313276.html Coronavirus: San Luis confirma la segunda muerte en el estado] {{in lang|es}} Mexico AS, 26 March 2020</ref> Citizens of [[Nogales, Sonora]] block border crossing from [[Nogales, Arizona]] in order to prevent the entrance of individuals with the virus infection and to prevent shortages of food, bottled water, toilet paper and cleaning supplies in local stores.<ref name=nogales>[https://www.univision.com/noticias/america-latina/el-mundo-al-reves-mexicanos-bloquean-frontera-para-que-no-entren-a-su-pais-estadounidenses-contagiados-por-el-covid-19?fbclid=IwAR1gSN0G6LXD9FTCI7YhZ-kw6nuTMRtbcIiSW7XtdulfaTCF5_tMcLZF7Gc Mexicanos bloquean frontera para que no entren a su pa\u00eds estadounidenses contagiados por el COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} by Isaias Alvarado, Univision Noticias, 26 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nAccording to the Secretary of Health, a plurality of the 585 people infected in Mexico, 70, are between 30 and 34 years old. People over 65 are second, followed by those 25 to 29 and 45 to 49. The states with the most incidents are Mexico City (83), Jalisco (64) and Nuevo Leon (57).<ref>[https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2020/03/27/tikitakas/1585334510_686136.html De 30 a 34, la media de edad de contagios por coronavirus COVID-19 en M\u00e9xico] {{in lang|es}} Mexico AS, 27 March 2020</ref>\n\nOn March 27 the federal government bought 5,000 ventilators from China as the government prepares for Phase 3 of the pandemic.<ref name=ventilator /> The total confirmed cases rose to 717; twelve deaths were reported, and there were 2,475 suspected cases.<ref name=\"27march\">{{cite web|url= https://politico.mx/minuta-politica/minuta-politica-gobierno-federal/ssa-presentar%C3%A1-informe-diario-sobre-coronavirus-en-m%C3%A9xico/ | title= Ssa: 717 casos confirmados de coronavirus y 2 mil 475 sospechosos |language=es |author=Pol\u00edtico MX|work=Pol\u00edtico.mx|date= March 27, 2020}}</ref> [[PROFECO]] (Office of the Federal Prosecutor for the Consumer) said it will fine merchants who unfairly raise the prices on household goods.<ref name=fine>[https://www.adn40.mx/noticia/mexico/notas/2020-03-27-08-26/multa-de-hasta-3-millones-a-quien-suba-el-precio-de-la-canasta-basica?fbclid=IwAR1oos_U7koXdgk--NAwgtzFNKNz6Pz7Yz9fxrGjg5n-j15kTP4WYl7_wuw Multa de hasta 3 millones a quien suba el precio de la canasta b\u00e1sica] ADN 40, 27 Mar 2020</ref> The governors of [[Governor of Nuevo Le\u00f3n|Nuevo Le\u00f3n]], [[Governor of Tamaulipas|Tamaulipas]] and [[Governor of Coahuila|Coahuila]] asked the federal government to close the border with [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|the United States]].<ref>[https://www.msn.com/es-mx/noticias/mexico/gobiernos-de-coahuila-nuevo-le%c3%b3n-y-tamaulipas-piden-a-amlo-cerrar-la-frontera-con-eu-por-COVID-19/ar-BB11P1Ie Gobiernos de Coahuila, Nuevo Le\u00f3n y Tamaulipas piden a AMLO cerrar la frontera con EU por COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} Sin Embargo, 27 Mar 2020</ref> \n\nOn March 28, Governor [[Omar Fayad]] of [[Hidalgo (state)|Hidalgo]] announced in a tweet that he tested positive for the virus and said that he was in self-quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/omar-fayad-gobernador-de-hidalgo-da-positivo-a-covid-19 | title= Omar Fayad, gobernador de Hidalgo, da positivo a COVID-19 |author=Redacci\u00f3n |work=El Financiero|language=es |date= March 28, 2020}}</ref> The [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Mexico]] said services should be held indoors with no more than twenty people present. They may cancel all [[Holy Week in Mexico|Holy Week]] celebrations if things do not improve.<ref>[https://www.milenio.com/politica/arquidiocesis-celebracion-semana-santa-puerta-cerrada Arquidi\u00f3cesis pide que celebraciones de Semana Santa sean a puerta cerrada] {{in lang|es}} by ELIA CASTILLO, Milenio, 28 Mar 2020</ref> In the evening the Secretariat of Health reported 131 new confirmed cases and four more deaths, raising the total to 848 confirmed cases and 16 deaths.<ref name=\"28march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/sube-a-848-los-contagiados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico/1372746 | title= Sube a 848 los contagiados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |author=Redacci\u00f3n |work=Exc\u00e9lsior|language=es|date= March 28, 2020}}</ref> Governor [[Cuauht\u00e9moc Blanco]] of Morelos announced the seventh case and first death due to COVID-19 in the state, a 37-year-old man who had recently traveled to the United States.<ref>[https://www.milenio.com/estados/coronavirus-confirman-el-primer-muerto-en-morelos-por-covid-19 Cuauht\u00e9moc Blanco confirma la primer muerte por COVID-19 en Morelos] {{in lang|es}} Milenio, 28 Mar 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.diariodemorelos.com/noticias/situaci-n-actual-del-coronavirus-covid-19-en-morelos?fbclid=IwAR2mfAxLsQlJ6o3tndIvL0n8fOLVDzTE0pSZewHYL9ReOGBi6UznpBcmv4Y SITUACI\u00d3N ACTUAL DEL CORONAVIRUS COVID-19 EN MORELOS] Diario de Morelos, 28 Mar 2020</ref> San Luis Potosi suspended wakes and funerals; the dead should be taken directly from the hospital to the [[crematorium]].<ref name=funeral>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-suspenden-funerales-por-covid-19-en-san-luis-potosi Suspenden funerales por COVID-19 en San Luis Potos\u00ed] El Universal, 28 Mar 2019</ref>\n\nTabasco Governor [[Ad\u00e1n Augusto L\u00f3pez Hern\u00e1ndez]] tested positive for COVID-19 on 29 March.<ref name=loppez_hernandez>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-gobernador-de-tabasco-da-positivo-covid-19-0 Governor of Tabasco tests positive for Covid-19] {{in lang|es}} El Universal, 29 March 2020</ref> Two tunnels with disinfectant spray were installed in the subways system of [[General Escobedo|Escobedo, Nuevo Le\u00f3n]].<ref>[https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/por-covid-19-colocan-tuneles-para-desinfectar-hasta-30-personas-por-minuto/1372842 Por Covid-19, colocan t\u00faneles para desinfectar hasta 30 personas por minuto] {{in lang|es}} by Aracely Garza, Excelsior, 29 Mar 2020</ref> The government of [[Yucat\u00e1n]] threatens fines of $86,000 pesos and up to three years in prison for individuals who have tested positive for coronavirus and do not self-quarantine.<ref>[https://noticieros.televisa.com/ultimas-noticias/coronavirus-multas-86-mil-pesos-personas-enfermas-aislen-yucatan/ Multas de 86 mil pesos a personas con coronavirus que no se a\u00edslen en Yucat\u00e1n] {{in lang|es}} Noticieros Televisa, 29 Mar 2020</ref> The state of [[Quer\u00e9taro]] registered its first death from COVID-19, a 56-year old man.<ref name=gov_tabasco>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-queretaro-registra-la-primera-muerte-por-covid-19 Quer\u00e9taro registra la primera muerte por COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} El Universal, 29 March 2020</ref> The same day 993 cases of COVID-19 and 20 deaths from the disease were confirmed.<ref name=\"29march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.publimetro.com.mx/mx/coronavirus-covid-19/2020/03/29/casos-muertes-coronavirus-mexico-29-marzo-2020.html | title= Suman 993 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 20 muertos|author=Publimetro |work=Publimetro|language=es|date= March 29, 2020}}</ref> Between 27 and 29 March, 566 Mexicans were brought home from other countries: 62 from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Colombia|Colombia]], 53 from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Ecuador|Eucador]], 299 from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Peru|Peru]], 28 from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Guatemala|Guatemala (via land)]], and 134 from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Cuba|Cuba]]. In turn, the Mexican government helped 86 people return to Ecuador, 99 to Peru, and 49 to Cuba.<ref>[https://www.msn.com/es-mx/noticias/mexico/en-dos-d%c3%adas-fueron-repatriados-576-mexicanos-suman-m%c3%a1s-de-8-mil/ar-BB11T5HG En dos d\u00edas, fueron repatriados 576 mexicanos; suman m\u00e1s de 8 mil] {{in lang|es}} La Jornada, 29 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the total number of cases of COVID-19 surpassed one thousand with 1,094 confirmed cases and 28 reported deaths in the country. In the evening, a national health emergency was declared in Mexico by Secretary [[Marcelo Ebrard]]; all sectors in the country are urged to stop most of their activities.<ref name=\"30march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/sociedad/coronavirus-30-de-marzo-mexico-supera-los-mil-contagios-de-coronavirus-suman-mil-94 | title= M\u00c9XICO, EN EMERGENCIA SANITARIA; SUPERA LOS MIL CASOS DE CORONAVIRUS |author=Redacci\u00f3n  |work=El Universal|language=es|date= March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn the early morning of 31 March, 50,000 test kits, 100,000 masks and five ventilators (donated by [[Jack Ma]] and the [[Alibaba Group|Alibaba]] Foundation of China) arrived at the [[Mexico City International Airport]].<ref>[https://aristeguinoticias.com/0104/mexico/llegan-a-mexico-50-mil-kits-de-pruebas-para-detectar-covid-19-donados-por-china/ Llegan a M\u00e9xico 50 mil kits de pruebas para detectar Covid-19, donados por China] {{in lang|es}} Arestegui Noticias, 31 Mar 2020</ref> Nurses in Jalisco have been forced to get off public transportation and physically attacked by people fearful of COVID-19. Medical workers there and elsewhere have been advised not to wear their uniforms outside the hospital.<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/31/bajan-del-transporte-a-enfermeras-en-jalisco-y-les-rocian-cloro-por-miedo-a-contagios-de-covid-19/ Bajan del transporte a enfermeras en Jalisco y les roc\u00edan cloro por miedo a contagios de Covid-19] {{in lang|es}} Infobae, 31 Mar 2020</ref> The same day the total confirmed cases of COVID-19 reached 1215 and one more death was reported. The government of [[Mexico City]] announced that 90% of the businesses in Mexico City would have to close because of the national health emergency declaration of the day before.<ref name=\"31march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-31-de-marzo-casos-de-covid-19-en-mexico-llegan-mil-215-hay-29-muertos | title= CASOS DE CORONAVIRUS EN M\u00c9XICO LLEGAN A MIL 215; HAY 29 MUERTOS |author=Redacci\u00f3n  |work=El Universal|language=es|date= March 31, 2020}}</ref> In [[Austin, Texas]], Public Health officials started investigating an apparent cluster of COVID-19 after 28 of 70 \u201cspring breakers\u201d (students at the [[University of Texas at Austin]]) tested positive following their trip to [[Cabo San Lucas]], [[Baja California Sur]] in early March.<ref>{{cite web|website=[[KXAN-TV]]|date=March 31, 2020|title=28 of 70 spring breakers on Mexico trip test positive for coronavirus |url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KXAN-TV}}</ref> The [[Mexican Social Security Institute|Mexican Social Security Institute (IMSS)]] in [[Monclova]], Coahuila, reported that 29 medical and nursing staff tested positive for COVID-19. No patients have been infected.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-mexico/coronavirus-infects-29-medical-workers-at-mexico-hospital-idUSKBN21J3W2 Coronavirus infects 29 medical workers at Mexico hospital] Reuters, 31 Mar 2020</ref>\n\n=== April 2020 ===\n\n==== April 1 to 15 ====\n[[File: Monterrey airport covid19.jpg |thumbnail|right|People wearing face masks at the [[Monterrey International Airport]] due to the COVID-19 pandemic.]]\nIt was reported on 1 April that seven migrants from Puebla residing in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in New York (state)|New York]] have died of COVID-19.  <ref>[https://www.animalpolitico.com/2020/04/siete-migrantes-poblanos-muertos-nueva-york-covid-19/ Suman siete migrantes poblanos muertos en Nueva York por COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} Animal Politico, 1 April 2020</ref> Authorities reported 46% of cases as recoveries, which represents approximately 634 recoveries. <ref name=\"youtube1\"/> In Coahuila, 21  health workers contracted the virus and one doctor died from it, bringing the number of deaths among doctors employed by IMSS to four. Nineteen of the 21 cases in Coahuila are mild and the individuals are ambulatory.<ref>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/several-health-workers-have-contracted-covid-19-mexico Several health workers have contracted COVID-19 in Mexico] {{in lang|en}} El Universal English, 1 Apr 2020</ref> Later the same day, 1378 cases and 37 deaths of COVID-19 were reported in Mexico.<ref name=\"1april\">{{cite web|url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-resumen-miercoles-1-abril-2020-secretaria-salud-muertos-contagiados-cifras/ | title= Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: Resumen mi\u00e9rcoles 1 de abril 2020 |author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |work=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico|language=es|date= April 1, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 2, 1,510 cases of COVID-19 and 13 more deaths related to the disease were confirmed by Mexican authorities.<ref name=\"2april\">{{cite web|url= https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/llega-a-50-la-cifra-de-muertos-por-coronavirus-y-van-mil-510-casos-confirmados | title= Llega a 50 la cifra de muertos por coronavirus en M\u00e9xico y van mil 510 casos confirmados |author=Redacci\u00f3n  |work=El Financiero|language=es|date= April 2, 2020}}</ref> In Mexico City, as hotels are forced to close, hotel guests are evicted from their rooms.<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/a-la-calle-hoteles-de-la-cdmx-desalojan-a-huespedes-ante-cuarentena-pandemia-covid-19-coronavirus-5052588.html \u00a1A la calle! Hoteles de la CDMX desalojan a hu\u00e9spedes ante Covid-19] {{in lang|es}} by Eduardo Torres, El Sol de M\u00e9xico, 2 Apr 2020</ref>\n\nOn April 3, 1,688 cases and 60 deaths were confirmed by the Secretariat of Health.<ref name=\"3april\">{{cite web|url= https://politica.expansion.mx/mexico/2020/04/03/los-casos-positivos-de-coronavirus-se-elevan-a-1-688-y-a-60-los-decesos| title= Los casos positivos de coronavirus se elevan a 1,688 y a 60 los decesos|author=Expansi\u00f3n Pol\u00edtica  |work=Expansi\u00f3n Pol\u00edtica|language=es|date= April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n=== [[Secretariat of Health (Mexico)|SALUD]] reported Mexico totals ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"display: inline-table; font-size:90%; text-align:right;\"\n|+ <big> As of April 3</big>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"  style=\"text-align:left; width:140px;\"|State\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Cases\n! Deaths\n! Recoveries\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:right; pad