2|Durango}}\n||8||1||3\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Nayarit}}\n||8||1||2\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Zacatecas}}\n||7||1||1\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Campeche}}\n||6||0||1\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Tlaxcala}}\n||8||0||1\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Colima}}\n||4||0||1\n|- style=\"text-align:left; padding-left:8px;\" class=\"sortbottom\"\n| style=\"width:360px;\" colspan=\"6\"| '''Source:''' \n<small>Secretar\u00eda de Salud (2020).<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gob.mx/salud/es/archivo/prensa?idiom=es&order=DESC&page=1 |title=Prensa &#124; Archivo &#124; Secretar\u00eda de Salud &#124; Gobierno |publisher=gob.mx |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref><br>\nGeological and Atmospheric Research Institute <ref name=\"iigea1\">{{cite web|url=http://iigea.com/amag/covid-19/ |title=COVID-19 Seguimiento \u2013 IIGEA |publisher=Iigea.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n</small>\n|}\n\n=== Cases per 100,000 inhabitants ===\n\n[[File:COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Mexico per 100,000 inhabitants.svg|thumb|right|251xpx| Map of the COVID-19 outbreak in Mexico per 100,000 inhabitants as of 2 April 2020.<br/>\n{{legend|#fee5d9|<0.1 per 100,000}}{{legend|#fcbba1|\u22650.1 per 100,000}}{{legend|#fc9272|\u22650.5 per 100,000}}{{legend|#fb6a4a|\u22651.0 per 100,000}}{{legend|#de2d26|\u22651.5 per 100,000}}{{legend|#a50f15|\u22652.0 per 100,000}}{{legend|#630606|\u22653.0 per 100,000}} {{legend|#450404|\u22655.0 per 100,000}} {{legend|#310303|\u22657.0 per 100,000}}]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"display: inline-table; font-size:90%; text-align:right;\"\n|+ <big> As of April 3</big>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"  style=\"text-align:left; width:140px;\"|State\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Cases\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" | Population{{efn|In 2015.}}\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" | Cases per 100,000 inhabitants{{efn|Calculated by dividing the number of cases by the total population of the 